item.description: An entry-level gaiter for the budget-conscious walker, the Outdoor Designs Stroll On Gaiter fits almost any boot and is tough enough for rough and tumble. Classic styling in hard-wearing nylon with a waterproof coating is comfortable and easy to adjust for the best fit. The rear zip and metal lace hook make donning them a breeze; Duke of Edinburgh's Award expeditionists and those wanting a decent gaiter at a great price will be more than happy with the Stroll On Gaiter.

item.title: Hoser 1
item.description: The Platypus Hoser 1L is the economical hydration system you can rely on - lightweight, tough and easy to use it's ideal for DofE and day walking. Platypus strive to make all their hydration systems the best in the world, letting you stay hydrated literally on the move. The Hoser lives up to this with its durable, BPA-free film and taste-free lining, welded together with a handy carry handle. With just the one opening for filling, cleaning and drinking it's very simple to use as well as to carry. Plus the threaded neck takes the screw-on hose, a push-pull cap or a closure cap for storing your water. Treated with Platypus' SlimeGuard antimicrobial technology and with the easy-clean HyperFlow bite valve it's also easy to maintain, making it the ideal choice for occasional or new walkers.

item.description: A loud whistle, made from a toughened plastic material, the Safety Whistle is an essential part of any outdoor or mountain survival kit. A whistle can be used to alert people if you are in distress. The internationally recognised distress signal is 6 blasts of the whistle with a 1 minute break and then repeated. The reply is 3 blasts with the same pause.

item.title: Map Measurer Plus
item.description: Digital map measurer with a modern waterproof design. Measures kilometres, miles and nautical miles. Given a known speed it can also calculate how long it will take to cover the rest of the route.

item.title: Scotland's Mountain Ridges
item.description: Ridges are epic, graceful carved walkways slung between summits, twisted spines of stone - these can be the most beautiful of mountain landforms. With elegant lines and giddy exposure, ridge climbs emit a powerful siren call, drawing us out onto the rocks. Life on the edge has a special quality, born of the contrast of empty space all around, and intricate detail in close-up. The crests are strangely irresistible. Scotland's ridges are among the finest mountaineering lines in the country, every one a unique adventure. The variety of these routes reflects the breadth of the mountain experience: a rich mix of summer scrambles, technical rock and challenging winter climbs. This book covers both the popular classics and some obscure gems, aiming to celebrate these thrilling climbs as much as to document them. The chosen selection spans the grade range, with routes to suit all levels of ability. Whether an earthbound hillwalker or an accomplished climber, Scotland's ridges cannot fail to stir your imagination.

item.title: Ski de Randonee (French edition) Hautes - Alpes
* Freney 40
item.description: The Grivel Freney 40 is both a mountaineering and ski touring bag. It is packed with useful accessories, stretch side pockets, front mesh pocket for the helmet, carrier for ice axes, ski protection in hypalon underneath the side compression straps with stops for the skis, elastic poles carrier retractable, top compression straps to reduce the volume and a dedicated interior pocket for the hydration system. The carry system uses the 'butterfly' system which adapts to the body of the carrier with a simple sliding weight distribution system and adjustable chest strap.

item.title: Thermolite XL
item.description: The Leki Thermolite XL is based on the original Thermolite performance pole, upgraded with SpeedLock adjusters and an extra long grip for full versatility. The same super-stiff aluminium alloy makes up the body of this sturdy lightweight pole. It's also got the same top-end moulded foam grip and premium wriststrap. The differences are most apparent when you're on changing terrain - with the SpeedLock adjusters you can quickly get the length right for every incline or decline. Or if it's only a short hill, just grab the extra-long extended grips to shorten them without stopping. An ultralight pole that's not short on features, the Thermolight XL was made to give you maximum performance and comfort on every challenge.

item.title: Smart Traveller Alu
item.description: Leki Traveller Alu Nordic Walking Poles Compact, lightweight, easy to carry Nordic Walking poles comprising 3 sections. Ideal for Nordic Walking enthusiasts to take on holiday or for hill walkers looking to add a fitness perspective to their days out.

item.description: A new guide to the rock routes in the popular Aiguilles Rouges situated on the southern side of the Chamonix Valley. Published in the same format as his last guide to the Envers Des Aiguilles; this new guide will prove to be invaluable to visiting climbers wishing to get out on the crags when the higher Mont Blanc massif is inaccessible due to bad weather.

item.title: Prolite Small
item.description: To go fast you've got to go light, but that's no reason to be uncomfortable - the Therm-A-Rest Prolite Small Mattress gives the best of both worlds. It's made from materials selected for packability and light weight, but you'd be wrong to think that it's all about the carry as 2.5cm of high-quality foam is more than enough for a good night's sleep. For minimalists and very young campers and backpackers, the Small size offers a way of cutting even more weight off your pack while retaining comfort and insulation at night. It's the precision cut-outs in the foam that make the Prolite the lightest and most compact mattress available without impacting on comfort. Shaped for longevity, the holes shave out the maximum possible weight while maintaining the support and insulation needed for three-season trips. Further aided by the tapered, rounded shape that cushions your shoulders and hips, the Prolite Small tips the balance at 310 grams and rolls down to only 8 cm diameter yet has enough warmth and comfort for anyone who doesn't suffer from cold feet. For a quiet night's sleep after a long day on the trail, you won't find a smaller, lighter mattress than the Prolite for the warmth.

item.title: Prolite Womens
item.description: To go fast you've got to go light, but that's no reason to be uncomfortable - the Therm-A-Rest Prolite Women's mattress gives the best of both worlds. It's the precision cut-outs in the foam that make the Prolite the lightest and most compact mattress available without impacting massively on comfort. The cushioning is also customised with fewer cut-outs under your hips and feet to provide extra cushioning and warmth where they're most needed. item.description: The Thermarest Compack Chair 20 weighs less than 200g, so it's hard to deny yourself the added luxury and convenience of a chair even when backpacking. Constructed from ultralight siliconised nylon with aluminium poles, it packs incredibly small and makes a rational as well as comfortable addition to even the lightest loads.

item.description: The Thermarest Trekker Chair 20 gives you the comfort of an upright or recliner seat at considerably lower weight and packsize. With adjustable straps between the seat and backrest you can choose the angle you recline at too, feeling comfortably supported whether you're cooking the dinner or chatting round the campfire. The lightweight way to add comfort to your extended backpacking trip; the Thermarest Trekker Chair lets you take a bit of luxury anywhere.

item.title: MicroRocket
item.description: The MSR MicroRocket stove takes full-on burning performance to the extremes of low weight and packsize. The little brother of the MSR PocketRocket is small enough to fit into an MSR Insulated or Stainless Steel Mug. But it unfolds with a few snappy moves into a miniature powerhouse capable of boiling a litre of water in three and a half minutes. It's also specialised to keep heating your food if the breeze gets up, with a WindClip protector on the focused burner head. And it's supplied with a smart piezo igniter whose fuel-gathering tube makes lighting the stove more reliable in the wind. The mountain marathon-runner's friend, the MSR MicroRocket lets you cut down on weight but not performance.

item.title: WhisperLite Universal
item.description: The MSR WhisperLite Universal stove gives you the best of both worlds for cooking on every trip, burning both canister gas and liquid fuels. Use gas canisters when they're available, set on a stand to enable liquid feed - great for cold conditions. But for longer, more remote trips and really cold weather the WhisperLite switches to burning a range of liquid fuels with a minimum of fuss. Better still, Air Control technology maintains the efficiency by optimising the fuel-air mixture for each type. The WhisperLite Universal backpacking stove is made for straightforward cooking - particularly when burning gas canisters it has the broad burner head and simmering capability for things like pasta and simple sauces. The lightweight but stable design folds to fit in larger pans and the stove is easy to maintain on a trip with Shaker Jet technology and simple disassembly. Specialised for everything, the WhisperLite Universal deserves its reputation as the most effective hybrid-fuel stove ever made.

item.title: WhisperLite Universal Combo
item.description: The MSR WhisperLite Universal Combo gives you the best of both worlds for cooking on every trip, burning both canister gas and liquid fuels. The Combo includes a mid-sized MSR fuel bottle, meaning that you just add fuel to get going. Use gas canisters when they're available, set on a stand to enable liquid feed - great for cold conditions. But for longer, more remote trips and really cold weather the WhisperLite switches to burning a range of liquid fuels with a minimum of fuss. Better still, Air Control technology maintains the efficiency by optimising the fuel-air mixture for each type. The WhisperLite Universal backpacking stove is made for straightforward cooking - particularly when burning gas canisters it has the broad burner head and simmering capability for things like pasta and simple sauces. The lightweight but stable design folds to fit in larger pans and the stove is easy to maintain on a trip with Shaker Jet technology and simple disassembly. Specialised for everything, the WhisperLite Universal deserves its reputation as the most effective hybrid-fuel stove ever made.

item.title: WhisperLite International Combo
item.description: The MSR WhisperLite International Combo is a legend in the multi-fuel game, letting backpackers cook simple meals efficiently using a wide range of fuels. The Combo includes a mid-sized MSR fuel bottle, meaning that you just add fuel to get going. Ideal for long trips when gas canisters aren't an option and for cooking in cold conditions or at altitude, the WhisperLite International is made tough but lightweight for expedition life. This proven backpacking stove is excellent for straightforward cooking; the broad burner head and moderate flame adjustment give you enough flexibility to simmer and heat foods like pasta, rice etc. The lightweight but stable design folds to fit in most pans and the stove is easy to maintain on a trip with Shaker Jet technology and simple disassembly. Optimised for the demands of extended trips abroad, the WhisperLite International marries efficiency to performance in one compact package.

item.title: WindPro 2
item.description: The MSR WindPro 2 stove is ultra-efficient, extremely stable for large pans and weighs less than 200g, plus it's got the flame control for proper cooking. Especially useful in cold conditions, the WindPro's remote canister stand enables liquid feed to the burner for more consistent performance through the life of the canister. The burner itself is also well-designed, with wide, sturdy legs and pot supports that take pans up to ten inches in diameter. The wide head spreads the heat so that with the fine control you can find the ideal level for whatever you're cooking. Highly efficient in more ways than one, the WindPro 2 is the lightweight option for elaborate and group cooking on the trail.

item.title: Carbon-Core Stake Kit
item.description: The MSR Carbon Core Stake Kit consists of four of the lightest full-strength tent pegs you can buy, no ifs, no buts. Resembling oversized nails, these little legends weigh less than 6g apiece, but are perfectly adequate for regular duty holding up your ultralight shelter. The key is hidden inside - the body of the peg is a carbon fibre tube, protected by an aluminium skin and with a hard plastic tip to penetrate the earth. While clearly they require a little care in pitching to achieve a long life, these remarkably pins will amaze you with their performance and help to shave even more grams off your minimalist pack.

item.title: Reflective Utility Cord Kit
item.description: The MSR Reflective Utility Cord Kit gives you fifteen metres of cord and four CamRing Tensioners; the possibilities are endless! Hanging tarps, replacing guylines and making temporary repairs or washing lines are some of the more usual uses of this handy stuff. 3mm in diameter for plenty of strength, it shows up brilliantly in the merest hint of torchlight. That makes it fantastic for marking your territory on a busy campsite or even making lightweight, night-visible zip pullers. You could even mark a trail to the natural bathroom or lay it round your tent to avoid people tripping over pegs. CamRing Cord Tensioners extend the possible uses, letting you create a great level of tension with ease. It's amazing what you can do with a bit of accessory cord - the Reflective Cord Kit is a must-have item in any standby repair kit.

item.title: Cam-Ring Cord Tensioners
item.description: If you don't get on with the average guyline runner, you need MSR CamRing Cord Tensioners to cut both weight and hassle in one. Sliding easily then locking securely, they're seriously easy to install and even easier to use. Simply thread your guyline through two adjacent holes, then in through the third, knot and you're done. The camming action provides tenacious hold in the windiest conditions and 6000-series aluminium barely weighs anything. A smart upgrade or reliable replacement for your lightweight tent.

item.title: Shock Cord Replacement Kit
item.description: Shock cords lose elasticity and begin to fail over time. Upgrade your tent poles with this premium shock cord replacement kit. The silicone-core shock cord provided with this kit outlasts natural rubber and remains elastic to -40 F/C. In addition, the kit includes detailed instructions and all the materials you need to replace the shock cord on a typical three person backpacking tent.

item.title: Universal Gear Loft
item.description: The MSR Universal Gear Loft fits almost any small tent, giving you extra space and making it easier to dry small items and keep your gear in order. On longer trips and overnighters alike, having a place to keep things like headtorches, snacks and socks can make a massive difference to tent life. Being mesh, this handy add-on shelf is particularly useful for keeping bits of gear in reach and fits virtually any tent thanks to the highly adjustable straps. It's even got a zipped pocket for the really small stuff. And the flexible wire frame lets it pack away in seconds. Simple but effective - the Universal Gear Loft is just the way good design should be.

item.title: Fabric Repair Kit
item.description: Quick, easy and permanent tent repairs are the preserve of the MSR Fabric Repair Kit, with two types of patches for all materials. Four clear patches work on flysheet and inner tent fabrics, covering tears and holes. NoSeeUm mesh patches stick to the mesh panels to maintain bug-free ventilation. Both are quick and easy to apply with pre-applied adhesive and stick permanently for reliable repairs in the field.

item.title: Universal Zipper Pulls
item.description: MSR Universal Zipper Pulls are a useful spare for your repair kit, letting you replace a damaged zipper pull or just enhancing the useability of your gear. Lightweight, reflective and easy to use in gloves or mitts, they're also quieter than metal zippers on tents when it's breezy. So you can banish the tapping from your dreams on windy nights. SImple to add - just lark's-foot the block through the attached loop and enjoy increased performance at lower weight too.

item.title: Big Air XP Package
item.description: The Black Diamond Big Air XP Package is an essential belay/rappel package featuring the multiple-friction ATC-XP. The ATC-XP maintains the silky-smooth feeding of the ATC but ups the braking power thanks to its grooved rope slots. The Mini Pearabiner scewgate biner is a compact, lightweight locker with a non-snagging keylock nose and a large rope-bearing surface for smooth belays and rappels.

item.title: Icon
item.description: With a modern, redesigned look and an unparalleled 200-lumen output, the all-new Black Diamond Icon Headlamp is our professional-grade light with a waterproof construction that's ready for anything you can throw at it. Whether you're rappelling an alpine route in a storm or participating in a SAR mission, this mega-bright headlamp's multiple modes let you customize your lighting needs to any situation and its IPX 7 waterproof rating makes it a true all-weather light. The Icon's red LEDs preserve your night vision and activate without cycling through the white mode, while the lock mode prevents accidental battery drain when the headlamp is in your pack.

item.title: Ion
item.description: The light that should be in every pack you own, the Black Diamond Ion provides ultralight, just-in-case lighting for anytime the sun goes to bed before you're back at the car. A single, 12-lumen SinglePower LED helps you make it down the rappels or find the trail, and the momentary switch prevents accidental battery drain when the Ion is in your pack.

item.title: Trail Shock Compact
item.description: A lightweight, do-anything pole with premium shock absorption thanks to our Control Shock Technology, The Black Diamond Trail Shock Compact Trekking Pole is a shorter, smaller-grip version of our Trail Shock and handles a short hike on the local trail as easily as a week-long trek on the Continental Divide. Control Shock Technology gives the pole progressive absorption and controlled rebound under any load, and dual FlickLock adjustments let you customize the pole length for any situation. The Trail Shock also features our interchangeable carbide Tech Tips, which can easily be swapped for our rubber Tech Tips (sold separately) to accommodate different trail surfaces.

item.title: Trail
item.description: From casual weekend jaunts to extended backpacking trips in the mountains, the Black Diamond Trail Trekking Pole expertly balances comfort, features and affordability. Dual FlickLocks offer complete adjustability to suit the terrain, while our interchangeable carbide Tech Tips are easily swapped for our rubber Tech Tips (sold separately) to accommodate changing trail surfaces.

item.title: * Traverse Lower Shaft
item.description: Replacement Lower shaft for the Traverse Ski Pole.

item.title: Trek glasses - black - spectron 4
item.description: The Trek's mission is simple: to achieve optimum performance while moving fast in extreme environments by providing highly technical, yet lightweight eyewear. For those committed to the outdoors via mountaineering, climbing and trail running, the Trek is the perfect combination of technical mountaineering principles and lightweight performance ergonomics. Detachable shields block lateral rays from intense glare as well as offer superior ventilation when necessary. Julbo's Flex Nose design and 360 adjustable temples provide optimum hold. The Spectron 4 lens is light but with excellent shock resistance. This versatile lens is suitable for all types of sports activities.

item.title: Trek glasses - blue - zebra
item.description: The Trek's mission is simple: to achieve optimum performance while moving fast in extreme environments by providing highly technical, yet lightweight eyewear. For those committed to the outdoors via mountaineering, climbing and trail running, the Trek is the perfect combination of technical mountaineering principles and lightweight performance ergonomics. Detachable shields block lateral rays from intense glare as well as offer superior ventilation when necessary. Julbo's Flex Nose design and 360 adjustable temples provide optimum hold. The Zebra photochromic lens darkens or lightens depending on the light's intensity. Its anti-fog coating, directly integrated via laser, guarantees maximum efficiency and long life. Zebra is recommended for mountain biking, trail biking, running, climbing, skiing, riding and other outdoor sports.

Peak Limestone Rockfax
item.description: May 2012 sees the publishing of the first single volume guidebook to Peak Limestone to have hit the shelves for many years. The last edition of Northern Limestone included much of Yorkshire too, this time round the Peak District gets its own dedicated coverage, with Yorkshire to follow. The book features expanded photographic coverage of the classic venues of Stoney, Cheedale and Water-cum-Jolly plus all the southern crags around Matlock, Dovedale and the Manifold Valley. The many routes that have been put up in recent years are included, plus a reassessment of the classics. On top of this there are a number of recently developed quarries that have become a magnet for sport climbers, including the ever-popular Horseshoe and Masson Lees. The striking crag-shots are backed up with full route descriptions and a superb set of action pictures that should inspire even the most jaded grit guru.

item.title: Ultra D Screwgate
item.description: Works wonderfully as a compliment to the Ultra O and Boa HMS screwgates for Rope Access as well as most other Working at Height applications.

item.title: Micro Vario Titanium Poles
item.description: Leki Micro Vario Titanium Poles are so light and easy to pack that you'll wonder how you ever got on strapping your sticks outside your pack. An evolution of the popular Leki Micro Sticks, Micro Varios offer a similarly lightweight solution with the added benefit of length adjustment to fine-tune them or for ascent. Despite the name, they're actually made from high quality aluminium for lightweight durability. Push-button assembly is quick and easy as well as highly reliable thanks to the kevlar-reinforced tensioning rope and the SpeedLock lever fastening provides 20cm of continuous length adjustment to get them the right length for you. Then when you reach the Via Ferrata or need to pack for your flight, just fold them down for a tiny 38 cm packed length, plenty small enough to go inside your pack or case. Lightweight doesn't have to mean compromising comfort either, since the hollow Aergon grip has no edges to dig into your hand and can be held in a number of ways. Versatile, strong and highly packable; the Micro Vario Ti pole is the lightweight hiker's dream pole.

item.title: ** Tupelo Womens Deep Water Blue US 8 - UK 6
Dynaclip 75cm Lanyard
item.description: The Beal Dynaclip is a dynamic lanyard specifically designed for clipping anchors on sport routes. Larks-foot it into your belay loop and use it as you would a sling, the big difference being that in a factor 1 fall the Beal Dynaclip reduces the impact force to less than half of that of a dyneema sling!

item.title: ex Distance Pedometer
item.description: Silva ex distance pedometer is compact, lightweight, easy to use and features a new, contemporary design with warm colour accents on a glossy white body. A newly designed robust clip secures the unit to the waist belt in the best possible way, but just in case, there's a safety lanyard to prevent accidental loss. The unique built-in filter function prevents the unwanted recording of occasional non-related movement during a walk, jog or day at work. The ex distance counts both steps and distance.

item.title: ex10 Distance Pedometer
item.description: The Silva ex10 Distance pedometer counts steps and measures distance. It's based on Accumotion, a new type of sensor which improves step counting. This sensor can be tilted up to an angle of 45, making step counting accurate when used on any shape of body. Silva ex10 Distance is carried around the neck, and has an integrated neck strap with safety release. The pedometer is water resistant, and has easy access buttons on the sides for setting functions. When the pedometer is not in use the display goes into sleep mode to save battery power.

item.title: Apex Ice Axe
item.description: A new, radically curved technical tool for hard icefalls and modern mixed climbing. The Apex is a superbly balanced precision tool: ready to tackle steep ice, massive mountain routes and mixed test pieces. The curved shaft provides an ergonomic hand position and impressive clearance around bulging ice. Can be used with leashes in traditional climbing mode, but excels without leashes for the more modern approach. The new one piece T rated Ice and Mix picks cover all the bases.

item.title: Apex Ice Hammer
item.description: A new, radically curved technical tool for hard icefalls and modern mixed climbing. The Apex is a superbly balanced precision tool: ready to tackle steep ice, massive mountain routes and mixed test pieces. The curved shaft provides an ergonomic hand position and impressive clearance around bulging ice. Can be used with leashes in traditional climbing mode, but excels without leashes for the more modern approach. The new one piece T rated Ice and Mix picks cover all the bases.

item.title: Fly Axe Mixed Pick
item.description: The iconic DMM Fly: the all-round climbing axe brought bang up to date for 2012. Tried and tested the world over, DMMs' go anywhere, do anything, classic winter tool has just got better. The original Fly has been used on the first ascents of challenging lines throughout the world for the last two decades. With this latest evolution, we've updated the tools with modern climbing in mind: an improved handle, a lower hand rest as standard, and the option to add on an upper rest for leashless climbing.

item.title: Cirque Alpine Hammer 50cm
item.description: The updated DMM Cirque Alpine Hammer provides the functionality you need in a second axe when walking becomes climbing. Designed to be fully trustworthy for self-arrest and a last option for belay anchoring, the T-rated pick and shaft combine with double-riveted construction to give the Cirque a reassuringly solid feel. The new hammer option even allows use when placing pitons in ice or cracks. The slightly curved shaft adds enough climbing functionality to this all-rounder for it to be practical as a second axe for steeper sections. Winter scramblers and walkers who enjoy some chilly verticality will love the versatility of the latest DMM Cirque.

item.title: Bulldog Ice Anchor
item.description: Winter climbing protection is often about making the best of what's available. In an ideal world, this would be ice screws in bullet hard ice and 'bomber' rock pretection throughout. However, our winter world is far from ideal and so inventive use of DMMs' Bulldog has been crucial in offering protection in frozen turf, thin icy cracks and marginal ice smears for over a decade. DMMs' updated bulldog keeps its versatility, but it's lighter, easier to place and easier to remove than it's predecessor.

item.title: Terrier Ice Anchor
item.description: A reliable companion through thin and testing times. The terrier is a perfect addition to the winter climbers rack. Micro-construction, thin seams, and turfy blobs can provide an oasis of security in a desert of winter madness.

item.title: * Apex/Switch Compact Mixed Hammer
item.description: Replacement Mixed Pick / Hammer for either the Apex or Switch ice tools. This is a direct replacement for the units fitted as standard to the tools changing the pick from an Ice Pick to a Mixed Pick.

item.title: * Apex/Switch Pick Weights + Bolts
item.description: Pick weights for bullet hard ice and customised balance on either the Apex or Switch tools.

item.title: PDA Case Large
item.description: For anything you need to keep 100% waterproof when you're exposed to the elements. Ideal for 1st Aid Kits, electronic equipment such as iPad's Kindles etc.

item.title: Boa HMS 3 Colour Pack
item.description: This is the 'Big Daddy' of lockers - the ultimate rigging biner and one which is super strong and super tough. It is large enough to accommodate several knots and has a very wide gate opening - just what you need in a rigging situation. All of which makes it a great centre use biner, but the story doesn't end there. Despite its name, the Big Boa is surprisingly light; by giving it an I-Beam construction we've reduced the overall weight by almost 25%. Add in the fact that it is easy to handle in gloves and the appeal to winter climbers is obvious.

item.title: Ultra O 3 Colour Pack
item.description: The Ultra O Screwgate could be described as the perfect aid climbing biner - it certainly performs remarkably well in the big wall environment and the I-Beam construction gives it an excellent strength to weight ratio. Perhaps multi day ascents, sac hauling, portaledges and extreme dehydration (eek!) are not your bag, but that doesn't mean you should turn your back on the oval biner design, far from it. At some point all of us will need to use a pulley system, most likely in a rescue situation. Oval biners are important because they allow pulleys to sit in a correctly loaded and equalised position. The symmetrical shape also stops them shifting under load and potentially dislodging a marginal gear placement. The locking gate adds a final element of security to the system.

item.title: * V9 Micro Lenser
item.description: The classic micro-torch from LED Lenser. Simple, elegant and so small you will hardly notice its presence on your key-ring.

item.title: Mont Blanc Super Cracks
item.description: The ultimate guide to Mont Blanc crack climbs, the guide covers Mont Blanc du Tacul, the Aiguilles de Chamonix, the Midi and the Plan des Aiguilles, the Envers des Aiguilles, the mer de Glace plus much more. The guide is in full colour with easy to follow topos and route descriptions as well as approach information. English language.

item.title: Core Glacier Gray
item.description: Superb construction and style. The Core range of altimeter products provide a huge array of features to help you enjoy your outdoor pursuits. Superb features include storm alarm which senses dramatic drop in barometric pressure, highly accurate altimeter, a variety of timers and of course a digital compass. Unique features of the core range: The pressure gauge operates in four distinct modes, including an automatic setting that senses vertical movement, switching between altimeter and barometer accordingly thus ensuring absolute accuracy. The compass features a rotating bezel for traditional use, or a one-touch function that allows you to sight, and follow a bearing.

item.description: Black Diamond Narrow Fit Crampon Bails are 8cm across. This is narrower by 0.5cm than the standard version and is suitable for any model within the current BD Crampon Pro Range. They are ideal for very narrow boots, especially in smaller sizes.

item.title: * Quasar 45
item.description: The Terra Nova Quasar 45 is a lightweight and compact mountaineering pack, combining Terra Nova's Matrix and Ultra fabrics. A lightweight, simple and compact pack, the Quasar has the extra durability needed for alpine or expedition use. Using Terra Nova Matrix fabric for high strength but low weight and reinforced with Dyneema/Cordura fabric for high wear areas - despite the extremely lightweight, durability has not been compromised. All stitching is with super strong Coat 50s thread, except bar tack points, which use Dyneema thread with a weight to strength ratio 10 times that of steel.

item.title: Nomic
item.description: The NOMIC allows the entire rock climbing repertoire to be transferred to ice. Thanks to its adjustable ergonomic handle, it offers multiple grip modes and limits the risk of snagging when switching hands. The ICE pick allows easy penetration in any type of ice, and pulls out easily. The modular head has two removable pick weights to balance the axe and propel it into the ice with an exceptional swing. The NOMIC can also be equipped with a hammer when placing pitons.

item.title: Ultralite Full Orange
item.description: The Vango Ultralite Full sleeping mat is a great value for money lightweight self-inflating foam pad. Ideal for staying light on your feet whether you're out wild camping or trying to find your perfect festival pitch. The Ultralite Self Inflating Mat will keep you warm and comfortable on the Black Mountains or the hills of Worthy Farm.

item.title: Hyperflow Bite Valve
item.description: The Platypus HyperFlow Bite Valve is a simple and efficient replacement part for your hydration system; leak-free to full-flow with merely a squeeze. Fitting the HyperFlow valve to Platypus Hoser and Big Zip systems is extremely simple - pull off the old mouthpiece and pop on the new. So easy in fact, that it's worth considering instead of doing the fiddly cleaning an old, furred-up bite valve. Of course, it's also useful if the original valve goes missing. Give your Hoser a new lease of life - fit a new HyperFlow Bite Valve for top performance and ease of use.

item.title: ! Canyoning in S Europe
item.description: Canyoning, the descent of natural gorges by a mixture of hiking, scrambling, swimming and abseiling is a spicy mix of the fun and the adventurous. This is a guide to canyoning in the limestone areas of the western Mediterranean, stretching from the Costa Blanca via the Pyrenees to Provence, Sardinia and Mallorca. Selective in nature, it includes a selection of recommended gorge descents, ranging from two-hour strolls to long-day aquatic expeditions. The more technical expeditions invariably involve abseiling and scrambling. Yet most canyons are within reach for anyone in possession of these skills and, in the case of wet canyons, a one-piece wetsuit. The friendly Mediterranean canyons are great places to 'learn the ropes', and the guide therefore provides a basic grounding in techniques and skills for the less experienced. Want to come and see what's around the next corner?

Ripper Standard
item.description: Try as we might to avoid it, there are occasions when we have to rely upon marginal gear placements. Whether that's a small, but crucial wire, or a suspect ice screw placement is not important. What matters is that we can improve the odds of it holding under impact. The answer to this conundrum is the Ripstop. These cleverly constructed quickdraws contain sections of weaker stitching that are designed to break when shock loaded. Each of the stitches that break absorbs some of the energy that would otherwise have been transferred into the marginal runner. The overall effect is to reduce the peak impact force, which is a rather fancy way of saying that your gear is less likely to rip. Keep one clipped to your harness; you never know when you'll need it next.

With a super-slick finish to let ice slide easily out of the core and technologically advanced thread design, the days of searching for a useable placement are gone.

item.title: Group Shelter 8-10 Bothy
item.description: Keep a group of up to ten people warm in case of an incident, or just to have lunch, in the Rab Group Shelter 8-10 Bothy. Lightweight windproof and waterproof polyester fabric traps air which is quickly warmed by the body heat of people sitting inside, creating a space much warmer than the outside and thus ideal for keeping a casualty or even the whole group warm while waiting for assistance. Simply shake out the whole bothy, duck underneath and sit on the waterproof seats around the bottom of the walls to keep it upright. If further support is needed, recesses in the roof take walking poles, while vents release excess vapour to prevent too much condensation forming inside. The bright colour and reflective piping keep you as visible as possible, and there's a window at each end so occupants can keep an eye on the outside world. Essential kit for group leaders and groups of friends in the hills, mountains or anywhere that shelters are few and far between, the bothy is supplied with a drawstring stuffsack for compactness and, weighing considerably less than a kilogram, is about the lightest of its type and size available.

item.title: Group Shelter 4-6 Bothy
item.description: In the Rab Integral Designs Group Shelter 4-6 Bothy you can keep a group of up to six people warm in case of an incident. Lightweight windproof and waterproof polyester fabric traps air which is quickly warmed by the body heat of people sitting inside, creating a space much warmer than the outside and thus ideal for keeping a casualty and the whole group warm while waiting for assistance. Whenever you have to stop, simply shake out the whole bothy, duck underneath and sit on the waterproof seats around the bottom of the walls to keep it upright. If further support is needed, recesses in the roof take walking poles, while vents release excess vapour to prevent too much condensation forming inside. The bright colour and reflective piping keep you as visible as possible, and there's a window at each end so occupants can keep an eye on the outside world. Essential kit for group leaders, the bothy is supplied with a drawstring stuffsack and, weighing considerably less than a kilogram, is one of the lightest of its type and size available.

item.description: The ultimate, smooth-clipping via ferrata set-up, the Easy Rider will have you efficiently climbing the "iron way" in style. The two Easy Rider carabiners have hot-forged bodies, gates and triggers with ergonomically contoured shapes for easy clip/unclip action and comfort. The biners also have a patent-pending internal locking mechanism and squeeze actuation, which provides excellent ease-of-use, eliminates hand pinch potential and greatly increases the ergonomic function of the carabiner. The Energy Absorption System (EAS) is stored in a durable, zippered pouch and is constructed using a compact, internal-sewn webbing system with a patent-pending sew construction. All the stove systems in the 25 series have two saucepans (1.75 and 1.5 litres), a 22 cm frying pan, windshields (upper and lower), a burner, a pan grip and a strap. Dimensions 22 x 10,5 cm.

item.title: Portable Mosquito Killer
item.description: A battery powered insect killer unit that can be used independantly in large tents, huts and hotels where mains power is not readily available. The unit slowly propels an odourless scent that is harmless to humans, but extremely effective against biting insects. The unit is supplied with a single cartridge that provides up to 7 nights* protection before it needs to be replaced (replacement cartridges are available separately). The unit requires 2 AA batteries which will also last approximately 7 nights. * 1 night = 8 hours approx.

Alpha KFS Set
item.description: The three piece AlphaSet has punched-out hexagonal holes in the handles to reduce weight while serving as a multipurpose tightening tool. This tough, lightweight hard anodized aluminium cutlery set comes with a mini carabiner to keep the pieces together.

item.title: Alpine 4 Pot Set
item.description: The MSR Alpine 4 Pot Set has the clean, simple durability of stainless steel in a weight-saving design that caters for a small group of hungry climbers. Tough enough for serious conditions and heavy use, the clever, nesting design keeps packspace to a minimum, particularly as the lid can double as a plate. This versatile set is optimised for efficiency, making it ideal for guides and frequent travellers who want to cook a lot of wide-ranging but straightforward meals during all sorts of trips. Three pans with fitting lids and a lightweight, interchangeable handle nest together, with MSR Alpine Plates and Bowls if you prefer. So if reliability trumps super-low weight in your book, the Alpine 4 Pot Set is the cook kit for your group.

item.title: Alpine 2 Pot Set
item.description: The MSR Alpine 2 Pot Set has the clean, simple durability of stainless steel in a weight-saving design that caters for two or more hungry climbers. Tough enough for serious conditions and heavy use, the clever, nesting design keeps packspace to a minimum, particularly as the lid can double as a plate. This versatile set is optimised for efficiency, making it ideal for guides and frequent travellers who want to cook a lot of wide-ranging but straightforward meals during all sorts of trips. So if reliability trumps super-low weight in your book, the Alpine 2 Pot Set is the cook kit for you.

item.title: Quick 2 System
item.description: The MSR Quick 2 System is the efficient cookware set for a pair of travellers - just add cutlery and you've all the gear for a simple meal. Two pans, two insulated mugs, two high-walled plates and a sturdy lid all pack together in one compact package, giving you the possibility of cooking basic meals on any trip. The set is particularly suited to use with the MSR WhisperLite and SuperFly series of stoves, since the hard-anodised aluminium pans spread the heat for fewer burnt bits in your pasta. The smaller pan is also non-stick for cooking sauces, veg etc. It's also easy to manipulate the pans around your workspace thanks to the Talon handle that clips securely but transfers easily between them. When packing, it also holds the lid of the large pan firmly on to avoid those annoying rattles. Smart design to make trail life better - the Quick 2 System adds versatility to your lightweight camp cooking.

item.title: Base 2 Pot Set
item.description: The MSR Base 2 Pot Set is the economical option for versatile two-person cooking on the trail, with two non-stick pans, lid and Talon handle. Lightweight aluminium keeps the weight down and the simple, straight-walled design lets the pans nest snugly together with the aluminium lid on top. There's a Talon handle that works interchangeably between the pans for reliable movement and clips the lid down for packing. Plus you get an ultralight PackTowl that sits between the pans to prevent scratching. It's the epitome of simple efficiency that can be built up into your perfect set with MSR DeepDish plates and insulated mugs. Choose the Base 2 Pot Set to keep versatile cooking within your weight and price budgets.

item.title: Titan 2 Pot Set
item.description: The MSR Titan 2 Pot Set makes the average lightweight pan set feel like it needs to lose weight, but is great for simple cooking for two. A nesting pair of ultra-lightweight titanium pans is the lightest way to equip yourself for cooking. With 2.5 litres capacity between them, plus a lightweight handle and a lid that doubles as a plate, you have all the cookware you need for a boil-only meal for two. And at only 272g there's no reason not to give yourself that option.

item.title: * Flex 3 Pot Set
item.description: The MSR Flex 3 Pot Set provides larger pots creating added volume for larger meals and car camping utility.

item.title: Snowshoe Maintenance Kit

item.title: ! Tour of The Queyras
item.description: NEW EDITION: A guide to a backpacking tour of the Queyras region of the Haute Alps on the border between Italy and France, following the GR58 and GR541 trails. The route includes the highest point reached on any grand randone with 24 cols above 2000m and options to climb up to 17 summits, five above 3000m. The Queyras is a dramatic, unspoilt region in the shadow of Monte Viso, sheltered to the west by the crins, and is one of the sunniest areas of the Alps. The absence of glaciers makes ideal hillwalking country, with several high mountain summits accessible to the ordinary walker and scrambler and it's one of France's best kept secrets!

item.description: Bedfordshire stretches across the plain of the Ouse to the Chiltern Hills Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty. It is a landscape of gentle hills and valleys, peppered with woodland, heath and parkland. There are over 1500 kilometres of public footpaths traversing the county that suit all standards and styles of walkers, from short circular walks to the Icknield Way and Greensand Ridge Walk. A further 600 kilometres of bridleways and byways offer many opportunities for cyclists and horse riders alike, ensuring this picturesque county can be enjoyed by all.

item.title: Alpine 1L Teapot
item.description: The MSR Alpine 1-Litre TeaPot nests inside 1.5 litre MSR pans, enabling those much-needed cups of tea wherever you go. Straight-sided for easy-packing efficiency, the big lid makes boiling water or even simple cooking quick and simple, not to mention the easy cleaning. The Alpine TeaPot also has a small but serviceable spout, making sure your drink ends up in your cup and not on the ground or, worse still, your hand. Plus foldaway handles on top allow quick and confident movement even when the pot is full. It's also useful for cooking porridge and heating wet meals efficiently when carried alone. Classic style that just works in all conditions, the Alpine TeaPot is reliably efficient wherever you are.

item.title: Flex Skillet
item.description: The MSR Flex Skillet adds frying to the repertoire of the Flex 3 and Flex 4 Systems and still lets them pack compactly. Sized to fit inside the Flex 4 System and on the outside of the Flex 3 System, it's a compact addition that vastly increases your meal options on a longer trip. Hard-anodised aluminium with a non-stick coating is easy to cook on and easy to clean, while the insulating Talon handle keeps you in control. Bring gourmet cooking into the wilderness with the Flex Skillet from MSR.

For information on the Grivel Range of Use, Click Here > Hide The Monte Rosa Crampons are essentially a basic, flexible winter walking crampon (think of a simplified G10) that is suitable for a range of B1-rated boots. The 3-Dimensional Relief Stamped (3DRS) front points offer superb torsional rigidity. The simple strap and plastic cradle configuration means that they are easy to fit on the go, whilst the flex bar is simple to adjust without the need for any tools.

Made to measure for the Havoc 200 and supplied with its own storage bag, your tent will thank you for buying its footprint too.

item.title: ! Froggatt to Black Rocks BMC
item.description: The crags stretching from Froggatt and Curber in the north to Black Rocks in the south is arguably the finest and most varied collection of outcrops on gritstone. This new guide replaces the 1992 Froggatt guide and the 1998 Chatsworth guide and brings the area bang up to date featuring over 2,200 routes and over 1,100 boulder problems; it's packed with full-colour action shots and a full set of well presented photo-topos.

item.description: An MSR TightLine Cord Tensioner reduces sagging and keeps the guys in the ground during wind plus it can be used with virtually any tent. Simply described, it's a guyline bungy, a shock-absorbing silicone band that attaches between the guyline and the tent so that when a big gust hits the impact on the peg is reduced. Simple and effective, it also assists with maintaining the ventilation gap between the inner and outer tents; vital for limiting condensation through the night. Pitch your tent with the TightLine and it will keep the tension on the fabric constant through the inevitable changes in temperature and humidity, so you'll always come back to a tent that's pitched as well as you left it.

item.title: Reactor 1L Stove System
item.description: Extreme cooking is made easier with the MSR Reactor 1.0L Stove System, designed for the remote and challenging conditions met by expeditionists. Ideal for soloists and pairs on a weight budget, the new one litre configuration provides all the excellent performance of its bigger brothers in a package as lightweight and compact as possible. Since the radiant burner head sits almost inside the base of the pot for cooking it is protected from the wind, a very high proportion of the heat goes into warming your food or melting snow - it boils half a litre of water in only 90 seconds! The litre pot can take the burner head and a 100 gram gas canister for transport and the burner is compatible with all sizes of Reactor pot giving you the flexibility for different types of trip. The proven best stove for the real world, choose a Reactor to eat quicker when it's cold.

item.title: Reactor 2.5L Stove System
item.description: Extreme cooking is made easier with the MSR Reactor 2.5L stove system, designed for the remote and challenging conditions met by expeditionists. Ideal for group use, the 2.5L pot lets you make a substantial meal for three in all sors of extreme conditions. Since the radiant burner head sits almost inside the base of the pot for cooking it is protected from the wind, a very high proportion of the heat goes into warming your food or melting snow - it takes around three minutes to boil a litre of water in almost any conditions! The burner head and a gas canister store inside the pot for transport and the burner is compatible with all sizes of Reactor pot giving you the flexibility for different types of trip. The proven best stove system for the real world, choose a Reactor to eat quicker when it's cold.

item.title: LuxuryLite UltraLite Cot Regular
item.description: THE ultimate camp bed, the Thermarest LuxuryLite UltraLite Cot is not only lighter and smaller-packing than any other, it's also a better sleep experience! The words camp and bed usually summon memories of squeaks, rattles, breakage and being tipped on to the floor, but this revolutionary new design makes sleeping off the floor a brand new game of cards. From the tiny package only 41cm long, a few practised moves and you're ready to be warm, comfortable and stable all night after a long day doing what you love. Instead of heavy steel poles and braces, the LuxuryLite Cot raises the game with lightweight alloy edge poles and cross-poles, secured with super-smart, super-robust and super-durable nylon feet that minimise damage to a tent floor and support the edges so you can even sit on the side without the whole thing bucking you off; you don't have to be circumspect when lying down! Plus, in case the remarkably low packed weight is still too much for a lightweight trip, you can strip it to a minimal setup that only weighs 900 grams but still provides excellent sleeping comfort! For paramount cushioning and extra warmth on a glamping or family camping trip team it with a Thermarest mattress, or simply enjoy the supportive comfort of a camp bed without the disadvantages.

item.title: NeoAir Dream Large
item.description: The Thermarest NeoAir Dream Large is as versatile as a mattress can be, going from compact storage to generous comfort in moments with minimal effort. Following the huge success of the DreamTime mattress, Therm-A-Rest have evolved the design to be even more useful, so there's no longer an issue with storage. Inside the fleecy cover, under the open cell foam top layer, is a custom-made NeoAir mattress, which deflates easily and completely by rolling the mattress. It's also simple to inflate as the storage sack can be used to push air into the mattress - it's as full as you need after only a few bagfuls. Tougher than the fast and light NeoAir mattresses for durability, the base can be used without the foam and cover for a convenient, even smaller package on a lightweight trip. All the pieces together are a full 10 cm thick, which is so comfortable and insulating as to make you forget you're lying on a hard floor or rocky ground. Then all you need is a great tent and you're fixed for outdoor adventures in luxury!

item.title: NeoAir Dream XLarge
item.description: All the comfort and warmth of the DreamTime in a smaller package - Therm-A-Rest's NeoAir Dream XLarge is as versatile as a mattress can be. Following the huge success of the DreamTime mattress, Therm-A-Rest have evolved the design to be even more useful, so there's no longer an issue with storage. Inside the fleecy cover, under the open cell foam top layer, is a custom-made, extra-wide NeoAir inflatable pad, which deflates easily and completely by rolling the mattress. It's also simple to inflate as the storage sack can be used to push air into the mattress - it's as full as you need after only a few bagfuls. Tougher than the fast and light NeoAir mattresses for durability, the base can nevertheless be used without the foam and cover for a convenient, even smaller package on a lightweight trip. Choose the XLarge size for and extra 13 cm of space to turn over, or just to spread out in your sleep. All the pieces together are a full 10 cm thick; it's so comfortable and insulating as to make you forget you're lying on a hard floor or rocky ground. Then all you need is a great tent and you're fixed for outdoor adventures in luxury!

item.title: MondoKing Large
item.description: So big it needs an over-sized valve to deflate and so comfy you'll barely believe it, Therm-A-Rest's Mondo King Large is the biggest and best self-inflating mat ever. Inside the soft fabric cover is a ten centimetre-thick pad of ultra-responsive foam, just waiting for you to sink into its depths and enjoy the contour-hugging support as you drift off to sleep. Nearly as wide as half a double bed and long enough for most sleepers to have warm feet all night, you'll have room to starfish (as much as you can in a sleeping bag anyway) and shift position in the night without falling off the edge. That's when it's inflated - open the valve, roll from the other end and you'll be amazed how small and light it packs. Rugged on the bottom to help prevent punctures and self-inflating in around fifteen minutes just by the power of the foam expanding, the Mondo King is ideal for base camp and family holidays where packsize is as important as comfort.

item.title: Ultra Mountain Z-Pole Basket
item.description: Specially designed to work with the new compacting poles, the Black Diamond Ultra Mountain Z-Pole Basket prevents the poles sinking into snow when walking. With two cut-outs to clip round the folded sections, the Z-Pole basket not only facilitates compact folding even when it's attached, but also keeps them folded when the poles are in your pack. Then when you get to a gradient, whip your poles out and the basket will keep your tips from sinking fathoms deep into snow or soft ground. A smart solution that works in all ways, the Ultra Mountain Z-Pole Basket makes your Ultra Mountain poles even better.

item.title: Magnetron RockLock
item.description: Imagine an HMS krab that autolocks infallibly, is easy to open but light and compact; imagine no more, the Black Diamond Magnetron RockLock is here. Even lighter than the equivalent twistlock, and significantly more intuitive to open, this super-secure carabiner makes setting up your belay device quicker and removes the risk of leaving the gate unlocked. Simply press the pivoted arms on either side of the gate to raise the magnets and the gate will open smoothly, with the subtly curved spine maximising the size of the opening. Release it, and the magnets click back into place with the steel insert on the snag-free keylock nose. With a square hinge end to hold the belay loop secure, the RockLock is your ideal belay carabiner at the wall and on the mountain.

item.title: Liquid White Gold
item.description: The Liquid White Gold liquid chalk from BLACK DIAMOND is specifically blended for climbing to keep sweat at bay, ensuring maximum grip no matter how hot or humid it gets.

item.title: Trail Lite Duo System
item.description: All the cookware for two in a compact package, the MSR Trail Lite Duo System enables you to feel that bit more at home even when space is at a premium. Nestled snugly inside the two litre aluminium pot come bowls and insulated mugs enough for a pair of backpackers to eat and drink in a civilised manner however long the trip. The hard-anodised aluminium and ceramic non-stick surface inside the pot protect it when cooking and packing and with a clear strainer lid you can see exactly when your water's boiling and thus save fuel. It's also very secure once packed, since the folding handle clips across the lid and the contents are snug inside to avoid annoying rattles as you walk. MSR's DeepDish bowls and lightweight double-wall mugs complete this versatile ensemble to add a bit of convenience to life on the trail.

item.title: Haute Route Chamonix to Zermatt
item.description: Undoubtedly the world's most famous ski traverse, the Haute Route takes skiers through the most prestigious ranges of the Alps, crossing the glaciers and high passes between Chamonix (F) and Zermatt(CH). Every year, around 4000 skiers undertake this unforgettable one-week traverse between the mountaineering capitals of the Alps. The introductory sections provide a wealth of practical advice on preparation, strategy and equipment, plus expert tips and a brief history of the traverse, all of which serve to highlight the alpine dimension of the Haute Route. Each stage is then presented in detail through comprehensive route descriptions, profiles of the climbs and descents, sketch maps and photos showing the route to follow.

item.title: Everest 1953 The Epic Story
item.description: In the only book to tell the real story of Everest 1953, Mick Conefrey reveals that what has gone down in history as a supremely well-planned attempt was in fact beset by crises ? both on and off the mountain. To succeed, team leader Colonel John Hunt and his team had to draw on unimaginable skill and determination, as well as sheer British ingenuity. Everest 1953 is not only a gripping true story of courage and adventure, but a long-overdue tribute to an under-appreciated British triumph. Revealing the answers to long-enduring controversies ? did Tenzing or Hillary actually reach the top first? ? and exploring the legacy of this great ascent, it is the perfect way to commemorate the year of the London Olympics.

item.title: Prolite XSmall
item.description: To go fast you've got to go light and the Therm-A-Rest Prolite Small Mattress makes this easy while keeping you comfortable and your body warm. It's made from materials selected for packability and light weight, but you'd be wrong to think that it's all about the carry as 2.5cm of high-quality foam is more than enough for a good night's sleep for practical types. Minimalist campers and backpackers, who do everything they can to shave weight, will appreciate the comfort and insulation that the XSmall size offers at such low weight. It's the precision cut-outs in the foam that make the Prolite the lightest and most compact mattress available without impacting on comfort. Shaped for longevity, the holes shave out the maximum possible weight while maintaining the support and insulation needed for three-season trips. The extra small size is perfect when you don't mind having your head and feet on your pack, your rope or your jacket in order to carry less. This means your shoulders and pelvis, the parts exerting the most pressure, are well-cushioned and insulated but you don't have the extra weight of the rest of it. Further aided by the tapered, rounded shape, the Prolite Small tips the balance at 230 grams and rolls down to only 8 cm diameter yet has enough warmth and comfort for all but winter conditions. For a quiet night's sleep after a long day on the trail, you won't find a smaller, lighter mattress than the Prolite XSmall for the warmth.

item.title: Luxury Map Regular
item.description: The Thermarest Luxury Map Regular mattress is a one-piece self-inflating mat made for sumptuous comfort, but it rolls up tight for transport too. That means that even women's hips and men's shoulders can sink into the die-cut areas, while the rest of the body is supported by the full-density foam everywhere else. Perfect for family- and car-camping,the soft face fabric won't irritate if your sleeping bag slips. And the whole thing rolls down to a convenient size to slot into your car boot. Ideal for frequent or occasional use under canvas, you'll discover new levels of camping comfort with the Thermarest Luxury Map.

In fact, the Base Camp is the lightest of the Thermarest Camp and Comfort self-inflating mattresses and is perfect for motorcycle touring and car-camping as well as family holidays. item.title: Reactor 2.5 Pot
item.description: The MSR Reactor 2.5L Pot adds capacity to your Reactor Stove System, extending its use to group situations. Easy to stir and with enough space to boil water for up to five dry meals at once, it also melts ice and snow without batting an eyelid. The large pot accommodates the Reactor's radiant burner head and a 227g canister inside for efficient transportation. The key to the Reactor system is the base of the pot, that accepts the burner head for minimal waste heat and maximum stability. The Reactor 2.5L pot brings this excellent performance to a versatile capacity, so you can take full reliability on an extreme group trip.

item.title: Reactor Stove 1.7L
item.description: Extreme cooking is made easier with the MSR Reactor 1.7L Stove System, designed for the remote and challenging conditions met by expeditionists. Ideal for varied use by soloists and groups of up to three people, the 1.7L pot strikes a balance between capacity and compactness, though of course you can add extra pots for more options. Since the radiant burner head sits almost inside the base of the pot for cooking it is protected from the wind, a very high proportion of the heat goes into warming your food or melting snow - it takes around three minutes to boil a litre of water in almost any conditions! The burner head and gas canister store inside the pot for transport and the burner is compatible with all sizes of Reactor pot giving you the flexibility for different types of trip. The proven best stove system for the real world, choose a Reactor to eat quicker when it's cold.

item.title: Hubba HP Green
item.description: The MSR Hubba HP gives one personreliable, free-standing shelter in three-season conditions, then packs to a minimal size and weight. You'll be frankly amazed at the speed and simplicity of pitching this sturdy backpacking tent, with MSR's unique hub design making assembly as easy as joining the dots. With the poles up, you have several pitching options: three-season protection with the inner tent; Fast and Light pitching with just the flysheet and footprint (available separately); or the inner tent alone in bug-ridden heat. And all enjoy excellent space and ventilation from MSR's excellent design. In every three-season situation, the Hubba HP gives you the protection you need at lowest practical weight.

The I-beam construction allows this 32g carabiner to amazingly hold 9kN with the gate open; an improved, deeper rope basket directs the load to the strongest point during a fall; and the shrouded nose reduces the chance of the gate opening when you really don't want it to. Ok, the DMM Phantom is lighter, but the Spectre works all year round - it's large enough to handle well even in winter gloves. If you count the grams but won't skimp on safety, you'll be more than satisfied with the Spectre 2.

9 out of 10 Climbers
item.description: 9 out of 10 Climbers make the same mistakes by Dave Macleod: A very comprehensive and no nonsense guide to training for climbing. Don't expect lots of pretty pictures or an easy ride. Do expect excellent, sometimes hard-hitting advice from the person possibly better qualified than anyone else to give it.

item.title: Kilimanjaro Trekking Guide
item.description: At 5895 metres (19,341ft) Kilimanjaro is Africa's highest mountain. Yet with no mountaineering skills necessary to reach the summit, even non-climbers can experience the thrill of climbing one of the world's greatest peaks. Taking you from the dusty plains of East Africa through jungle and moorland to the glacier-clad summit, this is one of the most beautiful and challenging treks there is. This Trailblazer book by Henry Stedman contains almost everything you could possibly want to know about the mountain, its ascent and its surroundings.

item.title: France Haute Provence Rockfax
item.description: A Rockfax book by Adrian Berry: The first in a series of selective guidebooks, France: Haute Provence presents many of the finest sport climbing destinations in the world together in one clear and colourful book. Covering all the best areas from the magnificent walls of Cse in the north to the impeccable climbing playground of Buoux to the south, this book has a lifetime's worth of climbing waiting on its pages.

item.title: ! Walks and Treks in the Maritime Alps
item.description: The first English-language walking and trekking guide to the Maritime Alps, on the border of Italy and France. 18 walks and 6 treks including a 5-day traverse of the Parc National du Mercantour and a 7-day traverse of the Parco Naturale delle Alpi Marittime, written by Alpine expert Gillian Price. Great for novice walkers and seasoned trekkers.

item.title: GR20 - Corsica
item.description: Guidebook to walking Corsica's GR20, known as the toughest waymarked trail in Europe. It makes a complete traverse through the high mountains, sometimes with hands-on scrambling. Covering 190km, it can be completed by fit walkers in about two weeks. The guide includes high- and low-level alternatives, plus extra mountain climbs.

item.title: Great Mountain Days in Snowdonia
item.description: A guide to 40 great mountain day walks and scrambles in Snowdonia, Wales, UK by Terry Marsh. Inspirational new routes for all abilities across the National Park in Snowdon and Moel Eilio, the Glyderau, the Carneddau, Eifionydd, Siabod and the Moelwynion, Rhinogydd (the Harlech Dome), Migneint and the Arans and Cadair Idris and the Tarrens.

item.title: ! Ecrins National Park
item.description: Guidebook to walking in the crins national park, France. The Massif des crins is one of the most spectacular regions in all the Alps. Most of the area is a national park, with summits over 3000m high. Well-marked trails and a network of alpine huts make the Ecrins accessible to walkers.

On reaching camp, simply flip the end of the casing, fit the rubber nozzle over the mattress valve and switch on for a perfectly inflated mattress in three minutes. At altitude this can be a huge saving of effort and in cold conditions prevents large amounts of water vapour in your breath from sitting inside your mattress. Lightweight and compact in your pack, the footprint also makes striking camp easier as there's no need to get mud everywhere when rolling up the inner. A small investment that could save a big expense, you'll feel better pitching your tent on its specifically-shaped footprint.

Both front and rear plastic harnesses are hinged from their respective retention posts and may be 'opened' to facilitate easy attachment to the boot, then closed securely once the boot is inside. The single strap closure system is so simple there's little need to include instructions. The New Classic is therefore ideal for rental programs and first time users. About the ultimate in lightweight simplicity that doesn't cost the earth - the Trangia Mess Tin adds an extra dimension to an old favourite.

The Tick Key
item.description: You need The Tick Key if you're ever outdoors; the quickest, easiest and safest way to remove a tick from people or pets to keep outdoor activities safe. Whatever you're doing outside, whether backpacking or approaching the crag, walking the dog or exploring a woodland, the ever-increasing risk of tick-borne disease is a gathering cloud thanks to milder winters. The crafty little things lie in wait on plants like grass and bracken and attach themselves to hair or clothing, crawling around until they find a nice spot for a meal. Though many bites are little more than a minor irritation, it's never pleasant to be sucked on by a small creature. Add to this the growing possibility of Lyme disease or any of several other unpleasant diseases, removing an attached tick as fast and in as low-risk manner as possible has to be the top priority when one is discovered. Enter The Tick Key. Small and flat to be unobtrusive on your keys or in your wallet, this remarkable one-piece device is every tick's nightmare. Simply place with the tick in the hole, slide the tick into the slot, pull and the whole tick is removed. That's the whole tick, mouthparts, body, legs and everything. It doesn't even give the little nasty a chance to infect the wound with its stomach contents. And you can retain the tick to show doctors in the case of a later reaction. Working equally well on dogs and cats as on humans it can also be attached to a pet's collar or your backpack so you don't need to remember it every time. As convenient as it is efficient and effective, The Tick Key is a small investment that could literally save a life. Please note: there are six different coloured anodised finishes. Orders for Tick Keys will be given a colour randomly unless you specify otherwise in the special delivery instruction box during the checkout process.

Wide Mouth Cantene 1.0L
item.description: The Nalgene Wide Mouth Cantene 1.0 litre offers all the benefits of a wide mouth bottle without taking up all that space when it's empty. The flexible container is easy to fill, easy to clean, easy to pack and above all, easy to drink from, keeping your liquids where you want them and tasting as they should. It even stands upright when it's full, thanks to the gusseted base. The wide mouth opening is welded into the top in such a way that, like the screw-top, it's guaranteed leak-proof. So the Cantene is just as reliable as the Everyday bottles, but more convenient. Nalgene's reason for the name: Convenient Nalgene Loop-top Closure. Available in different sizes up to 3 litres. Narrow- and Wide-mouth options available. Takes most water filters. Easy storage and collapsibility. Nice bottom gusset for standing upright. EEasy to read 'fill line' indicator.

item.title: Travel Kit with Carry Case
item.description: With all the rules about what you can take on a plane now, you need the Nalgene Travel Kit with Carry Case to ensure that all your liquids stay legal. Cheap flights save money but can be a hassle when you only have hand luggage to carry everything you need. Take a load off your mind by putting your liquids in these sturdy, lightweight pots and bottles. Sized for TSA regulations, you'll sail through security, then pack the six bottles back in the case, slip it in your bag and you're ready to fly. They're great for more than just your toiletries too. Minimalist campers can store oil and seasoning etc for cooking and soap for washing. Creams and pills are just as safe in the leakproof containers. And as they're dishwasher safe the use can change from trip to trip. Reliable, functional and packed in their own stylish zip and clip case, any traveller will love the versatility of the Nalgene Travel Kit.

item.title: * 3+ Avalanche Transceiver
item.description: The 3+ is a three-antenna device with a special extra function to first enhance your own safety. The intelligent position recognition system analyses the position of the antennas and automatically switches to the optimal transmitting antenna. There is no longer any such thing as the 'worst position'. The circular display lets you focus on the essentials. The distance to and the relative position of a victim. Always align the device to the arrow. The solid arrow and the central distance value keep you going in the right direction. The patented circular display shows you at a glance whether you are getting closer to the signal or moving away from it. With the precise distance value you can very effectively determine the distance to the buried victim and limit the area to be probed. The 3+ allows you to maintain an overview even with multiple burials. The number of victims is shown in the display. As soon as you have found the first one you can blend out their signal with the pin key. The victim is displayed as pinned and you can immediately continue with your search. Smart antenna technology enhances your own safety. Signal separation with pinning function. Very easy operation due to: clear control elements, precise real time display with directional arrows and circular display. Rubberized housing for protection and ergonomics. Display lighting for night searches, switchover in case of a follow-up avalanche, clear and optimized search acoustics, updateability.

All the essential tools - scissors, screwdriver, nailfile, tweezers and knifeblade - are here, plus a ballpoint pen and the piece de resistance: a 16GB USB 2.0 flash drive. Just the thing when you need to transfer a document between PCs or take it home to work on. That's when you're not removing staples and pushpins, opening letters and tidying up broken nails. So with the @work on your keys or attached to your work bag, you'll always have all those little things you just can't do without.

item.title: Peebol - Pack of 8
item.description: Introducing Peebol, the pocket-sized toilet that lets you 'go' anywhere. No, really! This is a genuine alternative to getting out of your sleeping bag during a freezing cold night in a tent. It works even better than a bottle, because the granules inside absorb liquid and change into a spill-proof biodegradable gel in seconds. You can even reuse them until full thanks to the watertight seal and 1 litre capacity. Then in the morning, just dispose of with the rest of your rubbish or keep it safely (and odour-free) in your pack pocket until you get back to civilisation. Peebol is made for both women and men. Ladies, use on its own or aim using a Shewee. They're also ideal for keeping in the car for emergencies like traffic jams or to avoid using service stations late at night. And it's hard to describe just how useful they are for children on car journeys. Compact and discreet enough for a daypack, handbag, pocket or first aid kit, you can take a Peebol literally anywhere and never be caught short again.

item.title: * Havoc 300 Footprint
item.description: Protect your inner tent groundsheet from rocky or wet ground and thorns, stones - the Vango Havoc 300 Footprint is tough but lightweight. A footprint is a small addition that makes a big difference to the longevity of your tent, with the added bonus of being significantly easier to clean after pitching on muddy, wet ground. Made to measure for the Havoc 300 and supplied with its own storage bag, your tent will thank you for buying its footprint too.

item.title: SEO3
item.description: The LED Lenser SEO3 Headlamp puts the power of LED Lenser torches on your head for useable light, hands-free. As colourful as your experience, the SEO3 uses three high-quality, bright LEDs to illuminate your world. Whether you're camping, running, night-walking or anything else, the SEO3's rotating head means it always has the perfect angle for what you're doing. It also sports a glare-free red LED, so you can keep your night vision even after reading your map. Plus it won't come on in your pack thanks to the keylock switch. At 96g and with a comfortable, adjustable and washable strap, you'll be happy to wear the SEO3 all night long when needed. Especially as it has a whopping beam distance of 40 metres - more than enough to keep you secure and active on the trail, on your bike or anywhere.

item.title: SEO7R Rechargeable
item.description: The LED Lenser SEO7R offers massive lighting performance in an eco-friendly rechargeable form that also keeps the weight amazingly low. Using the LED Lenser Advanced Focus System of a reflector and a lens, the SEO7R has a maximum luminosity of 220 lumens, but can still be used comfortably for ambient lighting (most headtorches have only a reflector, so can't focus the beam as effectively. Oh, and almost incidentally, the beam adapts to what you're looking at, switching from an ambient mode for reading the map to a brighter mode when you look into the distance. That's Optisense Technology for you! The rotating head lets you direct the beam wherever you want it too - whether ahead when cycling or in front of your feet on a night walk. It even starts at a decent angle - pointing slightly downwards. And with the continuous dimming that comes back on at the setting last used, you can customise your lighting to optimise power usage. All this, and it still only weighs 93 grams - plenty light enough for comfortable extended wear. Major power that's light and practical - that's the LED Lenser SEO7R.
