Hoolie 2 Footprint
item.description: Better protection and a longer life for your tent; the Wild Country Hoolie 2 Footprint adds extra beef against wet ground and sharp objects. Shaped to fit precisely underneath the sleeping compartment of your Wild Country Hoolie 2 tent, your groundsheet will thank you for laying out the footprint before pitching. You'll see the other benefits after a night on muddy, wet ground when you pack up a clean, dry inner tent. The footprint has its own storage sack that keeps it separate and compact in your pack... or on the outside when it's really mucky. A small addition that makes a big difference to the life of your tent; buy a Wild Country Hoolie 2 Footprint to make a difference to your camping life too.

item.title: Ultra Hyperspace
item.description: You can take the Terra Nova Ultra Hyperspace literally anywhere - from the poles to the highest peaks, it provides full protection at fantastically low weight. Shelters three hard-pushing expeditionists on a challenge one week, then a small family on the coast the next - this is a tent for all seasons and all trips, a sturdy, dry haven for the end of every day. In the same configuration as the long-established Terra Nova Hyperspace, this high-performance four-season tent uses materials with even higher strength-to-weight ratios. That means it weighs 25 percent less, while still providing full-on protection - very impressive! In fact, it's Terra Nova's lightest three-person mountain tent. However, it's not limited to cold conditions - pitch the inner only in hot, muggy weather for total ventilation without bugs. Space, practicality and two doors with vestibules; if you need your tent to be as versatile as you, the Ultra Hyperspace is where you want to be.

item.title: Superlite Bothy 2
item.description: The Terra Nova Superlite Bothy 2 keeps you and your buddy covered in an emergency, but it's barely noticeable the rest of the time. That's because Terra Nova have used extremely lightweight (though still ruggedly tough) siliconised fabric - the same as in their super-lightweight tents - that packs down small and weighs remarkably little. They've also cut out anything that's not absolutely necessary to shave off even more weight. So the Superlite Bothy doesn't have windows or sockets for placing your poles to support the roof. What it does have is true waterproof and windproof protection, so if you get caught out or just need somewhere warm to have a rest, you'll be shielded and visible in the Superlite Bothy 2.

item.title: Superlite Bothy 4
item.description: The Terra Nova Superlite Bothy 4 keeps you and your party covered in an emergency, but it's barely noticeable the rest of the time. That's because Terra Nova have used extremely lightweight (though still ruggedly tough) siliconised fabric - the same as in their super-lightweight tents - that packs down small and weighs remarkably little. They've also cut out anything that's not absolutely necessary to shave off even more weight. So the Superlite Bothy doesn't have windows or sockets for placing your poles to support the roof. What it does have is true waterproof and windproof protection, so if you get caught out or just need somewhere warm to have a rest, you'll be shielded and visible in the Superlite Bothy.

item.title: Aluminium Alloy V Peg - Pack of 10
item.description: Terra Nova Aluminium Alloy V-Pegs provide extra holding power for your tent in rough, windy weather but weigh only 11g each! High quality 7001-T6 alloy is strong and durable but very lightweight, making the pegs suitable for lightweight trips in potentially nasty conditions. The V-shape also aids strength, resisting the pull of a guyline or wind-blown tent by cupping the earth in front of it. Lightweight but effective, the perfect choice for any weight-conscious application.

item.title: Tent Cleaner 250ml
item.description: Keep your tent or bivi clean and performing at its best with regular washing in Terra Nova Tent Cleaner - water-based, safe and easy to use. While it's highly effective at lifting muck out of the fibres, it won't strip the DWR off your flysheet. In fact, Tent Cleaner will improve the performance of the water repellent coating by removing contaminants, particularly if your tent can dry in a warm place. As part of your tent maintenance regime, use Tent Cleaner to extend the useful life of your trusty tent or shelter.

item.title: Voyager 2.2 Groundsheet
item.description: The Terra Nova Voyager 2.2 Groundsheet Protector provides more pitching options and a longer life for your tent, adding extra protection from wet ground and sharp objects. Shaped to fit precisely underneath the sleeping compartment of the Terra Nova Voyager 2.2 tent, your groundsheet will thank you for laying out the Groundsheet Protector before pitching. You'll see the other benefits after a night on muddy, wet ground when you pack up a clean, dry inner tent. The Groundsheet Protector has its own storage sack that keeps it separate and compact in your pack... or on the outside when it's really mucky. A small addition that makes a big difference to the life of your tent; buy a Terra Nova Voyager 2.2 Groundsheet Protector to make a difference to your camping life too.

Oz Quickpack
item.description: The Oz Quickpack features 6 of Black Diamonds lightest quickdraws, now with the snag free benefits of their HoodWire Technology, making it ideal for trimming ounces on all-day gear routes and marathon sport pitches. Featuring the incredibly lightweight hot forged Oz carabiner on both the top and bottom combined with a 12cm Dynex dogbone, this quickdraw is perfect for any routes where a light rack is crucial. Now bringing keylock functionality to wiregate carabiners, the Oz uses a stainless steel wire hood to ensure snag free use.

item.title: Hoodwire Quickpack
item.description: The HoodWire Quickpack contains six of Black Diamonds HoodWire Quickdraws, now with hot-forged HoodWire carabiners on both the top and bottom. The Hoodwire features a stainless steel wire hood to give keylock performance and hassle free use, combining lightweight practicality with keylock functionality. The 14 mm Dynex dogbone provides a light, durable connection, and the Straitjacket insert ensures the bottom carabiner stays in the optimal clipping position.

item.title: Oz Wiregate
item.description: The Oz Wiregate is Black Diamonds lightest carabiner, now with the snag free benefits of their HoodWire Technology and engineered with an optimized shape. The incredibly lightweight hot forged Oz carabiner is perfect for any route where a light rack is crucial. Now bringing keylock functionality to wiregate carabiners, the Oz uses a stainless steel wire hood to ensure snag free use whilst retaining it's anti freezing benefits.

item.title: Hoodwire Rackpack
item.description: The Hoodwire Rackpack features six hot forged lightweight Hoodwire Wiregate carabiners with an innovative stainless steel wire hood. With its hot forged construction, no detail on the Hoodwire has been overlooked, including an optimized nose angle and a wide, rope bearing basket radius. Now bringing keylock functionality to wiregate carabiners, the Hoodwire uses a stainless steel wire hood to ensure snag free use. This lightweight, unique design makes for hassle-free, snag-free clipping and cleaning, plus it won't freeze up in alpine conditions or suffer from gate flutter.

item.title: Stopper Set Pro 1-13
item.description: The Black Diamond Stopper Set Pro No.1-13 features a full set of Stoppers sizes 1-13 on a Micron carabiner to protect everything from tip seams to finger cracks. Black Diamond Stoppers are designed with a transverse taper that permits sideways placements in flares and shallow seams. Anodized by size, they're quickly identifiable and rounded edges make for easy removal. Each Stopper is equipped with a durable, galvanized steel cable.

item.title: Stopper Set Classic 5-11
item.description: The Black Diamond Stopper Set Classic No.5-11 features a set of Stoppers sizes 5-11 on a Micron carabiner to protect everything from tip seams to finger cracks. Black Diamond Stoppers are designed with a transverse taper that permits sideways placements in flares and shallow seams. Anodized by size, they're quickly identifiable and rounded edges make for easy removal. Each Stopper is equipped with a durable, galvanized steel cable.

item.title: Micro Stopper Set 1-6
item.description: The Micro Stopper Set by Black Diamond comes with a set of Micro Stoppers sizes 1 to 6 on an OvalWire carabiner. Versatile thin crack protection the trapezoidal Micro Stoppers feature a subtle curve on their longest face for maintaining utility in near-parallel cracks while still catching on crystals and irregularities.

item.title: Nut Tool
item.description: The Black Diamond Nut Tool is a simple but highly functional protection removal tool. The Nut Tool is great at freeing fixed nuts, retrieving deeply buried cams and equally as effective opening a cold beer at the end of a days cragging. With an angled hook on one end and a bottle opener clip-in point on the other, the Nut Tool is an essential part of any trad rack.

item.title: Wired Hex Set 4-10
item.description: The Black Diamond Hex Set 4-10 features wired Hexes Numbers 4 to 10 racked on an OvalWire carabiner. This classic, lightweight, functional protection excels in rapidly widening cracks where cams might walk out. With a subtly asymmetrical cross-section, flat sides and slight end-wise taper, they offer three different widths when turned on their axes and another when placed end-wise. Easy to rack and place in bottlenecks, Hexes come equipped with durable, galvanized steel cables.

Drop Zone Crashpad
item.description: The Drop Zone Crash Pad is Black Diamond's mid sized all-rounder bouldering mat featuring an elastic flap closure for securely storing gear inside the pad. With a functional and durable design loaded with features, the Black Diamond Drop Zone Crash Pad is an ideal bouldering mat for all but the tallest of problems. The Drop Zone features 3.5 inches of high quality foam (both open and closed cell) to cushion your fall when things don't go your way, and two grab handles make for easy pad shuffles. Also featured is a quick closure elastic mesh flap that cinches down so you can shove your shoes, chalk bag, jacket and other essentials into the pad without having them fall out the bottom.

Alpine Carbon Cork
item.description: The Alpine Carbon Cork Trekking Pole by Black Diamond come with a lightweight carbon fibre construction, a natural cork grip, and dual FlickLock Pro adjustability, making it a top choice four season pole. For the weight conscious trekker, on the trail or in the snow, this lightweight, 100% carbon fibre trekking pole offers a super comfortable, premium cork grip and the supremely functional adjustability of dual FlickLock Pro. FlickLock Pro is the evolution of the trusted FlickLock design. The benefits of the classic FlickLock design remain: it's secure, fast and easy to use. The Pro's new low-profile, stainless steel design, however, provides a dramatic improvement in quality, feel and clamping force. The Pair also comes with two sets of baskets that can be easily tailored to trail or snow activities whilst the interchangeable carbide tips can be replaced or swapped for rubber Tech Tips (not provided).

item.title: Trail Pro Shock
item.description: The Black Diamond Trail Pro Shock is an updated version of the classic Trail Shock, now featuring the new low-profile FlickLock Pro locking mechanism. A lightweight, 4 season trekking pole, the Trail Pro Shock features Black Diamond's Control Shock Technology to help absorb the impact during use over all terrain making it suitable for anything from a short local walk to week long treks in the mountains. Control Shock Technology gives the pole progressive absorption and controlled rebound under any load, and dual FlickLock Pro adjustments let you customize the pole length for any situation. FlickLock Pro is the evolution of the trusted FlickLock design. The benefits of the classic FlickLock design remain: it's secure, fast and easy to use. The Pro's new low-profile, stainless steel design, however, provides a dramatic improvement in quality, feel and clamping force.

item.title: Womens Trail Pro Shock
item.description: The Black Diamond Women's Trail Pro Shock is an updated version of the classic Women's Trail Shock, now featuring the new low-profile FlickLock Pro locking mechanism. A lightweight, 4 season trekking pole, the Women's Trail Pro Shock features Black Diamond's Control Shock Technology to help absorb the impact during use over all terrain making it suitable for anything from a short local walk to week long treks in the mountains. Control Shock Technology gives the pole progressive absorption and controlled rebound under any load, and dual FlickLock Pro adjustments let you customize the pole length for any situation. FlickLock Pro is the evolution of the trusted FlickLock design. The benefits of the classic FlickLock design remain: it's secure, fast and easy to use. The Pro's new low-profile, stainless steel design, however, provides a dramatic improvement in quality, feel and clamping force.

item.title: Trail Pro
item.description: The Trail Pro Trekking Poles by Black Diamond combines a huge range of adjustment with a well balanced, durable design, making it a high performance, lightweight pole for everything from local day hikes to multi day treks in Nepal. The new Dual FlickLock Pro closures make for fast and secure adjustments to suit the terrain, and the dual density grip, padded wrist strap and foam grip extension ensure comfortable handling all year round. FlickLock Pro is the evolution of the trusted FlickLock design. The benefits of the classic FlickLock design remain: it's secure, fast and easy to use. The Pro's new low-profile, stainless steel design, however, provides a dramatic improvement in quality, feel and clamping force.

item.title: Trail
item.description: The Black Diamond Trail Poles are a simple, practical and easy to use pair of walking poles perfect for backpacking and day treks in the mountains. The Trail Poles expertly balance comfort, features and affordability with non-slip foam grip extensions on the handles for use in short steeper sections and Dual FlickLocks to offer complete adjustability to suit the terrain.

item.title: Womens Trail
item.description: The Black Diamond Women's Trail Poles are a simple, practical and easy to use pair of walking poles perfect for backpacking and day treks in the mountains. The Trail Poles expertly balance comfort, features and affordability with non-slip foam grip extensions on the handles for use in short steeper sections and Dual FlickLocks to offer complete adjustability to suit the terrain.

item.title: Trail Back
item.description: The Trail Back Trekking Pole is Black Diamond's no frills, 3-section pole with a simple, easy to use design perfect for backpacking and day treks on the trail. Providing reliable stability and easy adjustment for any on-trail adventure, the Trail Back Pole comes with Dual FlickLocks to provide total adjustability to suit the terrain at hand, and two kinds of baskets for 4-season customization.

item.title: First Strike
item.description: The First Strike Trekking Poles are Black Diamond's 4-season, fully-featured adjustable Children's poles. Featuring a FlickLock adjustment that allows the pole to grow with its owner or as the terrain dictates, whilst offering visual security that the pole is locked.

item.title: Trekking Pole Baskets
item.description: The Black Diamond Trekking Pole Spare Baskets are sold as a pair and are replacement 40mm wide baskets for trekking poles. The Baskets provide added grip and provide slight added protection to the poles.

item.title: Pole Spare Parts Kit
item.description: The Black Diamond Pole Spares Kit has virtually everything you could possibly need to tune up a ravaged set of trekking poles. In fact the only parts it doesn't have are replacement sections and handles, but if you've lost those you're going to need a new set of poles anyway! Everything else is there - pins and plugs to wristloops, tips and baskets for pretty much any BD pole in existence. Much of it would also fit poles of other brands, assuming similar sizes and fittings. It's all packed into a robust and portable organiser box and small parts are bagged in their own compartments inside. This makes it ideal for mountain leaders and tour companies who loan out ski or trekking poles or who frequently find themselves mending those of their customers. But equally, it's something that support crews on big and remote challenges shouldn't be without. Simply chuck the whole thing in with the poles and you're covered for all those little mishaps that just happen along the way. Contents 2 x Powder Basket 2 x Freeride Basket 2 x Compact Powder Basket 2 x 3/4 Basket 2 x Trekking Basket 14 x Wrist Strap to fit most BD Ski and Trekking poles from 2005 12 x FlickLock to fit diameters 13.4-18mm plus elliptic poles 2 x Z-Pole Basket 4 x interchangeable carbide and rubber tips for Z-Pole Baskets 4 x Long and Short Flex Tips 8 x Friction Plugs for probe poles Assorted strap pins, strap screws and FlickLock screws. 3 x Basket Ferrule

item.title: Sprinter
item.description: The Black Diamond Sprinter Headlamp has been designed for everyday pre-dawn/post-sunset use as a USB-rechargeable 75 lumen head torch and is ready for any trail in any weather. With a sleek rechargeable design and excellent fore aft balance, the 75 lumen Black Diamond Sprinter Headlamp is a versatile, all weather light that's ideal for high-impact use on the trail. A red taillight strobe in the rear adds visibility in urban areas, and the lithium polymer battery recharges through a USB port in 5 hours. The Sprinter's waterproof design keeps it going strong in any weather, and the regulated design provides constant illumination throughout the battery life.

* Ultralite Drysac M
item.description: The Lowe Alpine Ultralite Drysac is as it sounds; an ultralight, waterproof nylon stuffsac with roll top closure. Ideal for organising and protecting your outdoor kit in wet environments when weight counts.

item.title: Rucksack Liner Small
item.description: The Lowe Alpine Rucksac Liner is as it sounds; a durable, waterproof nylon liner with roll top closure and additional PU coating inside to aid weather resistance. Ideal for protecting your essential clothing and outdoor kit in wet environments .

item.title: Rucksack Liner Medium
item.description: The Lowe Alpine Rucksac Liner is as it sounds; a durable, waterproof nylon liner with roll top closure and additional PU coating inside to aid weather resistance. Ideal for protecting your essential clothing and outdoor kit in wet environments .

item.title: Megamat 7.5 LXW
item.description: The Exped MegaMat 7.5 LXW was made to prove that you don't need to be in a house to have a comfortable night's sleep. Amazingly light and compact for the weight, the MegaMat is perfect for car camping, house guests, glamping, base camp and much more. In fact in any sleeping situation that doesn't require carrying your gear on your back the MegaMat's wall-to-wall cushioned comfort and support will amaze and delight even the most hardened camping cynic. This self-inflating mat is 7.5 cm thick and is designed with 3 dimensional sidewalls, which ensure that the maximum thickness is carried from edge to edge. This also allows the mats to be placed side by side without a gap, making what is essentially a double bed. Furry tricot fabric on top is comfy next to the skin and the open-cell foam inside is cored horizontally so the whole thing packs down to only 21cm diameter. If you want the ultimate in convenient camping comfort without filling your car with mattress, th Exped MegaMat 7.5 LXW is definitely the sleeping mat for you.

item.title: Air Pillow XLarge
item.description: The Exped Air Pillow XL is a lightweight and packable sleeping option that, once used, will be hard to leave behind on any trip. The anatomically shaped design provides outstanding levels of sleeping comfort and head support whilst the provided stuffsack allows it to fit neatly in any pack.

item.title: Trek Long 3
item.description: The Trek Long sleeping mat by Vango is the perfect choice when durability, strength and affordability are paramount. The small pack size and light weight are ideal features when you need to carry your bed on your back. The 3cm diamond cut foam provides comfort at a reasonable weight whilst also insulating you from the ground, with the Diamond ripstop polyester providing a durable and tear resistant top and the non-slip base creating a comfortable night's sleep.

item.title: Folding Gas Stove
item.description: The Folding Stove by Vango is great for larger pans or use on unstable surfaces with its ultra-wide flame spreader ensuring your food is cooked thoroughly. It features a gas connection via a pipe with an ultra-wide flame spreader and a handy storage box. The folding stove also has an impressive boiling time of 1 litre in 6 minutes and it's compact size and lightweight means carrying it with you on the trail is never a problem.

item.title: LuxuryLite UL Cot Large
item.description: The Thermarest LuxuryLite UltraLite Cot Large is not only lighter and smaller-packing than any other camp bed, it's also a better sleep experience! The words camp and bed usually summon memories of squeaks, rattles, breakage and being tipped on to the floor, but this revolutionary new design makes sleeping off the floor a brand new game of cards. For a start, this Large version adds extra length and width for taller sleepers to avoid the dreaded overhang. From the tiny package only 43cm long, a few practised moves and you're ready to be warm, comfortable and stable all night after a long day doing what you love. Instead of heavy steel poles and braces, the LuxuryLite Cot raises the game with lightweight alloy edge poles and cross-poles, secured with super-smart, super-robust and super-durable nylon feet that minimise damage to a tent floor and support the edges so you can even sit on the side without the whole thing bucking you off; you don't have to be circumspect when lying down! Plus, in case the remarkably low packed weight is still too much for a lightweight trip, you can strip it to a minimal setup that only weighs just over a kilo but still provides excellent sleeping comfort! For paramount cushioning and extra warmth on a glamping or family camping trip team it with a Thermarest mattress, or simply enjoy the supportive comfort of a camp bed without the disadvantages.

item.title: NeoAir All Season Medium
item.description: A mat for all seasons; the Thermarest NeoAir All Season Medium mattress features the award-winning NeoAir design with extra warmth and toughness. It's the most versatile of the NeoAir range, made for hard use all year round but still light and compact enough for lightweight backpacking. Now supplied with a NeoAir Mini Pump for simple and quick inflation, the Triangular Core Matrix is highly effective in recycling and reflecting your body heat when you're camping on cold ground as well as providing a resilient and supportive pad that hips and shoulders can sink into. With an R-value of 4.9 you'll be cosy well down into the minus figures and tough fabric on the upper and lower surfaces ensures that you can rely on the NeoAir All Seasons to keep you warm on every trip.

item.title: NeoAir All Season Regular
item.description: A mat for all seasons; the Thermarest NeoAir All Season Regular mattress features the award-winning NeoAir design with extra warmth and toughness. It's the most versatile of the NeoAir range, made for hard use all year round but still light and compact enough for lightweight backpacking. item.title: NeoAir Trekker Regular
item.description: The redesigned Thermarest NeoAir Trekker Regular Mattress is a robust, three-season sleeping pad for trips requiring high performance, durable gear. The addition of ThermaCapture technology gives this iteration a considerable advantage over its predecessor, boosting warmth while actually saving weight. But the NeoAir Trekker is still outstandingly durable, with tough, puncture-resistant fabrics top and bottom and that classic NeoAir construction. The straightforward square shape gives you plenty of room to spread out, with 6.3cm of depth for your shoulders to sink into. If hard-wearing is one of your favourite words, the Thermarest NeoAir Trekker has to be your favourite camping mattress for all your three-season trips.

item.title: NeoAir Trekker Large Torso
item.description: The redesigned Thermarest NeoAir Trekker Large Torso Mattress is a robust, three-season sleeping pad for trips requiring high performance, durable gear. The addition of ThermaCapture technology gives this iteration a considerable advantage over its predecessor, boosting warmth while actually saving weight. But the NeoAir Trekker is still outstandingly durable, with tough, puncture-resistant fabrics top and bottom and that classic NeoAir construction. To save weight, the Large Torso size cushions your body only, leaving your feet and legs to rest on something like your pack or rope. The straightforward square shape gives you plenty of room to turn over, with 6.3cm of depth for your shoulders to sink into. If hard-wearing is one of your favourite words, the Thermarest NeoAir Trekker has to be your favourite camping mattress for all your three-season trips.

item.title: NeoAir Trekker Large
item.description: The redesigned Thermarest NeoAir Trekker Large Mattress is a robust, three-season sleeping pad for trips requiring high performance, durable gear. item.title: Trail Pro Womens Regular
item.description: The Thermarest Trail Pro Women's Regular Mattress is now even better for year-round use when backpacking, trekking or family camping. Now incorporating ultra-compressible, lightweight foam, the same foam as was used in the Thermarest 40th Anniversary Mattresses, the updated Trail Pro is lighter and more packable to go pretty much anywhere you go. The shape has also been tweaked, with straightened sides on the torso to facilitate gap-free mating of two mattresses. The Women's shape also has less foam cut out for a warmer sleeping surface. But you still get the support throughout that let your shoulders and hips sink in while suporting in between. A great all-rounder for a wide range of activities, the Trail Pro is Thermarest's warmest and most comfortable self-inflating mat.

item.description: The Thermarest Trail Pro Regular Mattress is now even better for year-round use when backpacking, trekking or family camping. item.title: Trail Lite Womens Regular
item.description: With the Thermarest Trail Lite Women's Regular mattress you can have your cake and eat it - a lightweight, packable mat with great sleeping comfort. A real all-rounder, now with an improved shape to avoid that annoying gap between a couple's mats. This version is a little smaller, warmer and more supportive in places to cater to a lady sleeper's needs. Die-cut foam is the secret to the Trail Lite's success, letting the mat pack to a compact 15cm diameter but still loft up to 3.8 cm thick. Small enough for your backpack but tough and comfy enough for family camping, this is a three-season winner for a variety of sleeping situations.

item.description: With the Thermarest Trail Lite Women's Large mattress you can have your cake and eat it - a lightweight, packable mat with great sleeping comfort. item.title: NeoAir Camper Regular
item.description: The Thermarest NeoAir Camper Regular is about the toughest and most comfortable air mattress you'll find that still packs down to a convenient size. 7.6cm thick and with durable, puncture-resistant fabric, you can feel the benefit of the NeoAir structure from the moment you lie down. That's because the double layer of interlocked triangles not only insulates you from losing heat to the ground, it also makes a comfortable and stable platform to sleep on. But it's still light and packs small enough to be a touch more luxury on an overnight or backpacking trip. The most durable NeoAir yet, the NeoAir Camper is a versatile sleeping surface that won't let you down.

item.description: The Thermarest NeoAir Camper Large is about the toughest and most comfortable air mattress you'll find that still packs down to a convenient size. 7.6cm thick and with durable, puncture-resistant fabric, you can feel the benefit of the NeoAir structure from the moment you lie down. item.title: Ridgerest Solar Regular
item.description: The Thermarest RidgeRest Solar Regular is the warmest, most comfortable foam mat in the Thermarest range, with smart ThermaCapture technology. A thicker, more insulating version of the RidgeRest SOLite, the Solar increases the amount of body heat that's retained instead of being lost to the ground. The silver coating both reflects heat back to where you need it and adds durability. Combined with the 2cm closed-cell foam in a comfort-adding ridged pattern, this allows the RidgeRest Solar to provide durability and functional comfort at low weight and cost.

item.title: Ridgerest Solar Large
item.description: The Thermarest RidgeRest Solar Large is the warmest, most comfortable foam mat in the Thermarest range, with smart ThermaCapture technology. A thicker, more insulating version of the RidgeRest SOLite, the Solar increases the amount of body heat that's retained instead of being lost to the ground. The silver coating both reflects heat back to where you need it and adds durability. Combined with the 2cm closed-cell foam in a comfort-adding ridged pattern, this allows the RidgeRest Solar to provide durability and functional comfort at low weight and cost.

item.title: Prolite Large
item.description: To go fast you've got to go light, but that's no reason to be uncomfortable - the Therm-A-Rest Prolite Large Mattress gives the best of both worlds. It's made from materials selected for packability and light weight, but you'd be wrong to think that it's all about the carry as 2.5cm of high-quality foam is more than enough for a good night's sleep. It's the precision cut-outs in the foam that make the Prolite the lightest and most compact mattress available without impacting on comfort. Shaped for longevity, the holes shave out the maximum possible weight while maintaining the support and insulation needed for three-season trips. Further aided by the tapered, rounded shape, the Prolite Large packs down small but offers extra length and width for taller sleepers or those who prefer a bit more space. For a quiet night's sleep after a long day on the trail, you won't find a smaller, lighter mattress than the Prolite for the warmth.

item.title: Trekker Pillow Case Eggplant One Size
Trekker Pillow Case Grey One Size
NeoAir Torrent Air Pump
item.description: The tiny Thermarest NeoAir Torrent Pump punches above its weight when inflating your mattress in cold conditions or at altitude. Designed exclusively for use with Thermarest valves, this battery- or DC-powered pump exerts positive pressure, inflating a NeoAir mattress to your chosen firmness in as little as 100 seconds. As space-efficient as a NeoAir mattress itself, the NeoAir Torrent Pump adds ease and convenience to extreme low weight.

item.title: Instant Field Repair Kit
item.description: The Thermarest Instant Field Repair Kit replaces the Fast and Light Repair Kit, being the minimum equipment you need to fix your bed on a trip. Complete with clear adhesive patches, Glue Dots and cleaning supplies, it allows you to make semi-permanent repairs to your mattress as soon as damage occur. And more importantly, the short cure times let you use the mattress again almost immediately. Instructions are included to help you make a good repair.

item.title: Permanent Home Repair Kit
item.description: The Thermarest Permanent Home Repair Kit replaces the Universal Repair Kit, providing all the supplies you need to repair damage to your mattress. Accidents sometimes happen on hard trips, but when they happens to your Thermarest mattress all is not lost. This fully-equipped kit helps you make a good and long-lasting repair so your faithful sleeping mat can live to fight another day. Because the adhesives included are chosen for their strength they have mandatory 24 hour cure times, so this is definitely a kit for using at home and for more significant damage than the Instant Field Repair Kit. Instructions are included to make the process as simple as possible.

item.title: Reactor 1.7L Pot
item.description: The MSR Reactor 1.7L Pot adds versatility to your Reactor Stove System, working for everything from solo snow melting to group meals. The mid-size pot accommodates the Reactor's radiant burner head and a 227g canister inside for efficient transportation. The key to the Reactor system is the base of the pot, that accepts the burner head for minimal waste heat and maximum stability. The Reactor 1.7L pot brings this excellent performance to a versatile capacity, so you can take full reliability on every trip.

item.title: SuperFly
item.description: The MSR SuperFly sits in the sweet spot for cooking on expedition; it's big enough to be controllable for cooking, but still packs small and light. It's not short on power either, boiling a litre of water in around three minutes. And it's extremely versatile thanks to the Multi-Mount fitting that allows the SuperFly to run on almost any self-sealing canister you'll find. Made to allow effective cooking of simple meals, the adjustable flame and wide burner head will make it possible to eat proper food on every trip. And the wide supports are great for large pots but twist away for packing. MSR's most versatile canister stove, the SuperFly makes eating easy on the trail.

item.title: Alpinist 2 Pot
item.description: The MSR Alpinist 2 Pot minimises the weight and packspace of cooking for two; a lightweight but robust and well-designed pan for rapid cooking. Designed for simple duties like boiling water, melting snow and heating simple meals in remote locations, the 2.4-litre pan holds plenty of water for two or three and will spread heat to help avoid burning. With a strong Talon handle and aluminium strainer lid it's designed to pack as easily as it handles. Plus there's plenty of space inside for MSR plates and bowls or a compact stove to keep everything together in one simple package. Great design at minimal weight, the Alpinist 2 Pot is the ideal option for fast and light trips.

item.title: Flex 3 System
item.description: The MSR Flex 3 System gives you the flexibility to cook like you do at home and eat in comfort and style - eating kit for three that packs brilliantly. Two decently-sized pans are hard-anodised for a durable, resilient finish, with a non-stick cooking surface in the smaller pan for sauces, vegetables and other potentially sticky foods. Packed neatly inside and between these are enough high-sided plates and stainless steel insulated mugs to keep a group of three eating in comfort throughout a long trip. They're even colour-coded, so everyone can have their own set. And the smart Talon handle locks the lid in place so you can rely on it staying together for transport. Customisable with extra mugs and plates and the MSR Flex Skillet, it's all the kit you need when decent food is the order of the day.

item.title: Flex 4 System
item.description: For group cooking and compact transport you need the MSR Flex 4 System, with all the pots and pans for four people to eat in style. Even elaborate meals are possible using this extensive system, which is made for road trips, group catering and base-camping. Two hard-anodised aluminium pans, one with a hefty 5.3 litre capacity, give you plenty of options for cooking for up to four hungry hikers at the end of a long day. Serving is just as easy, with four colour-coded DeepDish Plates and Stainless Steel Insulated Mugs giving each person their own personalised set. The plates are particularly clever, with high walls that keep the food on the plate and off your lap. And at the end of the meal, it all nests together for secure transport. Smart cookware that makes trail life better both for cookers and eaters.

item.title: Deep Dish Plate Medium Blue One Size
Deep Dish Plate Medium Green One Size
Deep Dish Plate Large Red One Size
Pan Handler
item.description: Light pan handle as supplied with most MSR pot sets, ideal as a replacement or extra handle.

item.title: Heat Exchanger
item.description: With an MSR Heat Exchanger your food is ready quicker and takes less fuel to heat up. Attached easily and securely round an MSR 1.5- to 2-litre pan the corrugated fins both shield the flame from wind and transfer what would otherwise be wasted heat into your food. So it takes less time and less fuel to do the same amount of cooking, which can only be a good thing! Simple but effective, the Heat Exchanger makes a big difference on base- and car-camping trips.

item.title: Pole Repair Kit
item.description: The MSR Pole Repair Kit is an important back-up for a long, remote trip, when an unuseable shelter can cause a whole world of trouble. Most standard backpacking tent poles can be shored up with the lightweight sleeve that simply slides into place. For other types, the adjustable splint makes a temporary repair to any pole of 7mm to 20mm diameter. Turn a mountain into a molehill if your tent pole fails - the MSR Pole Repair Kit offers peace of mind when shelter really counts.

item.title: Shelter Wash and Restore
item.description: MSR Shelter Wash and Restore is your tent's key to a longer life, particularly if it's got a bit whiffy. Water-soluble, safe and easy to use, this two-part set gently cleans the fabrics then restores the Durable Water Repellent (DWR) coating on any tent. Simply dilute the Shelter Wash as directed, rub in with a sponge and rinse, then spray with Shelter Restore, rub in and leave to dry before packing. It's as easy as that to keep down musty smells from mildew or just from long use. If you've ever spent a night in a smelly tent you'll know just how useful MSR Shelter Wash and Restore can be!

item.title: Reflective Guy Line Markers
item.description: Avoid those spectacular trips over guylines with MSR Reflective Guyline Markers; simple idea, big difference to safety. Attaching easily with hook and loop fastenings they'll stay in place all night, warning passers-by that your guylines are in their path. Which will hopefully keep you undisturbed as well as them safer. They also make it easier to lay hands on dark-coloured gear in the night. A handy little addition to enhance your tent.

item.title: * DromLite 2L
item.description: The MSR DromLite 2L Bag is the little sister of the seriously rugged Dromedary Bag; at 30 percent lower weight it's made for fast and light adventures. Stripped of everything except an eyelet for hanging and the handle that makes filling simple, the DromLite Bag is more streamlined and packs smaller. But it's still rugged, with 200 denier Cordura nylon fending off all comers. A straightforward, well-designed water carrier for when failure is not an option.

item.title: * DromLite 4L
item.description: The MSR DromLite 4L Bag is the little sister of the seriously rugged Dromedary Bag; at 30 percent lower weight it's made for fast and light adventures. Stripped of everything except an eyelet for hanging and the handle that makes filling simple, the DromLite Bag is more streamlined and packs smaller. But it's still rugged, with 200 denier Cordura nylon fending off all comers. A straightforward, well-designed water carrier for when failure is not an option.

item.title: SweetWater Microfilter
item.description: When out on the backpacking trail you need the MSR SweetWater Microfilter to guard against contaminants in your drinking water. Effective against everything except viruses (which can be killed using chlorine-based treatments), so bacteria, protozoa, particulates and chemical contaminants don't stand a chance against the granulated activated carbon microfilter. The SweetWater is amazingly easy to pump but still packs down small and light for carrying. It also gets rid of taste and odour... it's in the name really! Clean it in the field to maintain the 1+ litre/min flow rate and pump straight into your drinking bottle for convenience. For the most reliable water possible, you can't do better than the SweetWater Purifier System.

item.title: AutoFlow Gravity Filter
item.description: The MSR AutoFlow Gravity Filter takes the effort out of cleaning your drinking water when base-camping in remote areas. Instead of pumping, simply hang the bag high to let gravity do the work of pushing water through the hollow fibre filter. Et voila, your water is free of bacteria, protozoa and particulates and can be put straight into your drinking bottle or reservoir using the universal adapter. The four-litre capacity and fast filtering makes the AutoFlow ideal for group use, plus the quick and easy tool-free cleaning is invaluable on long trips. Reliable water without the work, the AutoFlow Gravity Filter takes the effort out of safe hydration.

item.title: MiniWorks Maintenance Kit
item.description: The MSR MiniWorks Microfilter Maintenance Kit contains everything you need to give your vital filter pump a periodic once-over. Cleaning and checking the pump every so often and certainly after each trip will help it stay in full working order for longer. This handy, compact kit has all the consumables including silicone lubricant and O-rings so you don't have to worry if one's looking dodgy. A worthwhile investment to extend the life of your microfilter.

item.title: Big Zip LP 1.5L
item.description: The Platypus Big Zip LP 1.5L adds easy filling to the other benefits of a lightweight hydration system, with a SlideLock closure for security. Now flatter when filled, the new Big Zip LP fits better in the hydration pocket of your rucksack and has a quick-release hose and shut-off valve for peace of mind when it comes to leaks. Of course, it also comes with Platypus' SlimeGuard antimicrobial treatment and is BPA- and taste-free as standard. The Platypus you know, with extra reliability; the Big Zip LP is the one to choose for big trips.

item.title: Big Zip LP 3.0L
item.description: The Platypus Big Zip LP 3.0L adds easy filling to the other benefits of a lightweight hydration system, with a SlideLock closure for security. Now flatter when filled, the new Big Zip LP fits better in the hydration pocket of your rucksack and has a quick-release hose and shut-off valve for peace of mind when it comes to leaks. The three-litre capacity also gives you the option of an even flatter package if you put your two litre requirement in it. Of course, the Big Zip LP comes with Platypus' SlimeGuard antimicrobial treatment and is BPA- and taste-free as standard. The Platypus you know, with extra reliability; the Big Zip LP is the one to choose for big trips.

item.title: Hoser 3.0L
item.description: The Platypus Hoser 3.0L is the economical hydration system you can rely on - lightweight, tough and easy to use it's ideal for DofE and day walking. Platypus strive to make all their hydration systems the best in the world, letting you stay hydrated literally on the move. The Hoser lives up to this with its durable, BPA-free film and taste-free lining, welded together with a handy carry handle. With just the one opening for filling, cleaning and drinking it's very simple to use as well as to carry. Plus the threaded neck takes the screw-on hose, a push-pull cap or a closure cap for storing your water. Treated with Platypus' SlimeGuard antimicrobial technology and with the easy-clean HyperFlow bite valve it's also easy to maintain, making it the ideal choice for occasional or new walkers.

item.title: Water Tank 2.0L
item.description: The Platypus Platy Water Tank 2.0L holds a day's water in an easy-to-carry, highly useable design. Despite it packing almost flat, the horizontal-style water carrier unzips at the top to take two litres of water. Use the carry handles to get it from source to wherever you want it and also to help with pouring from the screw top spout. Compatible with the Platypus GravityWorks filtration system, it's ideal for lightweight backpacking and base-camping alike and will see you through many an adventure at minimal weight.

item.title: Water Tank 6.0L
item.description: The Platypus Platy Water Tank 6.0L holds all the water two people need around camp in an easy-to-carry, highly useable design. Despite it packing almost flat, the horizontal-style water carrier unzips at the top to take a massive six litres of water. Then you can use the carry handles to get it from source to wherever you want it and also to help with pouring from the screw top spout. Compatible with the Platypus GravityWorks filtration system, it's ideal for lightweight backpacking and base-camping alike and will see you through many an adventure at minimal weight.

item.title: Platy Preserve 800ml
item.description: Oh, the luxury of a glass of wine after a hard day's trekking; brought to you by the Platypus PlatyPreserve wine-carrying soft bottle. If you'd love to take a wine with you, but the glass bottle puts you off, this is the solution for you. Rolling down to a tiny size when empty, the PlatyPreserve does exactly what its name suggests, keeping a bottle's worth of wine fresh and flavourful for several weeks. Simply fill, squeeze out the air and seal for an easily transportable package. You may even find yourself using it at home. Add class to even the roughest camp meal - just remember to bring something to drink it from!

item.title: Bite Valve and Tube Insulator
item.description: Winter-ise your hydration system - add a Platypus Bite Valve and Drink Tube Insulator to prevent ice blockages between you and your water. It's pretty straightforward - the flexible foam tube slides easily over your Platypus Hoser or Big Zip drinking tube to keep its contents liquid for longer in freezing conditions. Then pop on the Bite Valve Cover to protect your mouthpiece from solidifying, replace the mouthpiece and you're ready for the cold stuff. Invaluable for staying hydrated on the move in the winter months.

item.title: In-Line Shut-Off Valve
item.description: When water is vital, it pays to secure against losing even a drop with the Platypus In-Line Valve in the hottest and most remote situations. Fitting easily into any Platypus drinking tube (with the aid of a sharp knife), the In-Line Valve offers the benefit of stopping the water before the mouthpiece, but keeps the end of the tube straight. Operated by a simple turn valve, it's the assurance you need to keep the focus on your activity.

item.title: Ergo Shut-Off Valve
item.description: When water is vital, it pays to secure against losing even a drop with the Platypus Ergo Shut-Off Valve in the hottest and most remote situations. Fitting easily into the end of your Platypus Hoser's drinking tube, it not only provides the security of a shut-off valve, but also turns the mouthpiece at right-angles for comfort and convenience. Smooth, easy flow control lets you see in an instant whether it's locked or not. Upgrade your Hoser or replace the valve on your Big Zip, the Ergo Shut-Off Valve does everything you could want it to.

item.title: Big Zip SL Drink Tube Kit
item.description: Replace your Big Zip SP's hose when cleaning doesn't do the job any more, with the Platypus Big Zip Drink Tube Kit including Quick Disconnect fitting. After long use, your Platypus Big ZIp hydration system might get beyond the help of even the most thorough clean. But there's no need to dump the lot, just swop the hose for the Big ZIp Drink Tube Kit and get going again. Fitting straight into the Quick Disconnect outlet and featuring the 90-degree Ergo Shut-Off Valve, it will give a new lease of life when your old tube dies.

item.title: Quick Release Kit
item.description: The Platypus Quick-Release Kit works with any hydration system with a quarter-inch tube, letting you keep the hose in place while filling. Designed to shut off when the male part is removed, this handy add-on can save you significant amounts of time in getting your pack sorted each morning. Instead of unthreading and rethreading the hose through ports, elastic straps, clips and more, simply release the hose, remove, fill and replace the reservoir and you're away. Easy to install in the Platypus Hoser or any other screw-top system, the Quick-Release Kit is an investment that will save you time every time.

item.title: Rock Star Helmet - Orange
item.description: The Camp Rock Star Orange is a versatile and affordable helmet perfect for large groups and any other situations where helmets are bound to get beat up. Durable injection-molded polyethylene shell. Nylon inner structure with fast and easy slide adjustment system.

item.title: Motormonkey
item.description: The PowerTraveller Motormonkey is a handy little gadget for long car journeys with your devices - the world's smallest USB adapter. Sitting in your car's socket, it's virtually unnoticeable since the face lies flush. It's clever enough to stay there without draining the battery, then if you connect an Apple device, it changes its power settings accordingly. It even shuts down once your iPod, smartphone, camera battery or headtorch is fully charged. Reduce the number of cables you carry and keep your kit juiced, the Motormonkey is the silver bullet for electronics on the move.

item.title: Solarmonkey Adventurer
item.description: The Solar monkey adventurer is a slimline, compact 2-panel solar charger with a 2500mAh internal lithium polymer battery. The clamshell design offers optimum weight-to-efficiency at just 265g and the 2 solar panels output 3 watt max. The adventurer features auto-load, self sensing switching technology, meaning when a device is connected, the adventurer will automatically start to charge your device and will optimise the charging parameters required. The polysilicon solar panel offers photovoltaic efficiency up to 17% and features a USB 700mA @ 5v output, fully supporting Apple iPhones, iPads, iPods, mobile phones and other 5v gadgets such as portable games consoles, handheld GPS systems, e-readers, etc. The solar monkey adventurer also has a solar energy detection feature which activates the incorporated state-of-the-art MPPT (maximum power point tracker) technology, allowing it to charge your device more efficiently in low light conditions. The solar panels will charge the internal battery in just 12 hours in optimum light conditions. Users can also charge the solar monkey adventurer and their devices simultaneously, thus saving time. You recharge the adventurer by the mains (UTC sold separately) via the DC 5v 600mA socket or via the solar panel. Whilst the adventurer is being charged the LED light will be red, once the internal battery is fully charged, this light will turn green. The kit comes with a handy carabiner so it can be attached to tents or rucksacks and is made from high quality durable materials which make it both water and shock resistant - perfect for the outdoor adventurer and the busy traveller. We've also included the white Apple monkeytail cable to allow easier connection to your Apple devices, as well as a specially designed travel case. The travel case is made from a tough, condura-type material and features a thermal insulation layer to protect the solar monkey adventurer from the elements. The technical details inside the case include thin elasticated straps on both halves to hold the adventurer securely in place whilst the solar panel is open and an elastic self-securing buckle that fits through the hinge slots of the adventurer, ensuring it is held in place. The top half of the case features a netted storage area for cables, etc and the tough, waterproof zip keeps the solar monkey adventurer protected. External features include a hang loop at the top of the case and belt loops at the rear. Packed full with protection features including short-circuit protection, overload protection and low voltage protection and importantly, thermal insulation battery protection giving an operating temperature range of -10 to 90 degrees C, the solar monkey adventurer adds an exciting new dimension to the existing Powertraveller range.

item.title: Powermonkey Discovery
item.description: The Powermonkey Discovery is a sleek, compact and stylish portable charger that will make sure you can keep your favourite gadgets going whilst on the move. Featuring a state-of-the-art 3500mAh lithium polymer battery, the sleek powermonkey discovery offers users real power on the move. Housed in a stylish full aluminium case with 6 high bright pin point LED lights, the powermonkey discovery will recharge an iPhone twice, standard mobile phones 3-4 times, or give iPods / MP3 players up to an additional 120 hours playtime. It is also compatible with e-readers, Sat Navs, handheld games consoles, portable GPS systems and more! Please note, iPhones and iPads will require the USB sync/charge cable supplied by Apple. The powermonkey discovery portable charger is supplied with a USB to micro USB charging cable only. The recessed LED lights indicate the power stored in the unit (6 green lights show the unit is fully charged) and when unit needs to be recharged the last LED will turn red. Recharge the powermonkey discovery via your computer's USB port. Control of the powermonkey discovery is via the metal on/off button located at the top of the unit, whilst the USB port has built-in self-sensing technology which allows the unit to optimise the charging parameters for the iPhone and other smartphones. Recharge the powermonkey discovery via your computer's USB socket using the included USB to micro USB charging cable.

item.title: Beginners Guide for Climbers
item.description: The Rockfax Beginners' Guide for Climbers is the instructional guide for young people starting out on the wall. Fully endorsed by the National Indoor Climbing Achievement Scheme (NICAS) and the Mountaineering Council of Scotland, it's a fun way to learn the basics of climbing between sessions. Illustrated throughout with attractive cartoon characters, the Beginners' Guide takes you in an easily understandable way through tying in and belaying to wall skills, equipment and knots. In fact, it covers everything you need to know for NICAS Levels 1 and 2, plus some of the Level 3 skills. It even comes with a length of cord so you can practice as you read. The first guidebook written specifically to appeal to a younger audience, it's a must-have for any budding climber learning the ropes.

item.description: The Black Diamond Refillable Chalk Shot contains Black Diamond's uncut White Gold pure chalk, a specific blend for climbing performance. By keeping your skin dry, this magnesium carbonate (MgCO3) chalk improves your grip on rock, indoor walls and whatever else you're climbing on really. Packing it tightly into a fine mesh bag makes it go a lot further and this mesh bag is refillable, giving you an effective product that's also efficient and economical. Perfect for ticking off your next climbing endeavour.

item.title: Powergorilla
item.description: The PowerGorilla by PowerTraveller is the next step in portable rechargeable power sources, able to provide an extra 2-5 hours of power on your laptop or up to 20 hours on various other electronic devices (see feature list). The PowerGorilla is an easy to use portable charger that will work with devices up to 24Volts, simply select the required voltage from 5V up to 24V using the one touch button, indicated on the LCD screen, and connect your device to start charging. This varied voltage enables the PowerGorilla to work with anything from your laptop to your iPod (other mp3 devices are available). There is also the option for you to charge the PowerGorilla from the mains power supply at the same time it is powering your laptop or even charge multiple devices at once through daisy-chaining. The PowerGorilla uses input voltage auto recognition technology which means that if you use your own AC laptop charger (between 16 - 24V only), it will automatically detect the voltage level and set the LCD display accordingly. The sleek, aluminium casing has additional shock resistant rubber protection strips, making it both stylish and practical. Having been field tested in some of the most extreme conditions in the world, including Afghanistan, Madagascar, Zambia, Antarctica and Norway, the PowerGorilla is a reliable and efficient power source designed to be taken on all your adventures, wherever they may take you.

Simply anchor the carabiner to any hook, D-ring, or loop, and feed your cord through the cam until you've reached the desired level of tension. Pull firmly, and the cam locks into place and stays that way until you release it by rotating the cam.

Micro Vario Carbon Lady
item.description: Leki Micro Vario Carbon Lady Trekking Poles are so light and easy to pack that you'll wonder how you ever got on strapping your sticks outside your pack. An evolution of the popular Leki Micro Sticks, Micro Varios offer a similarly lightweight solution with the added benefit of length adjustment to fine-tune them or for ascent. These particular poles are super-lightweight but even stronger than aluminium because they're made from pure carbon. Push-button assembly is quick and easy as well as highly reliable thanks to the kevlar-reinforced tensioning rope. The SpeedLock lever fastening provides 20cm of continuous length adjustment to get them the right length for you. Then when you reach the Via Ferrata or need to pack for your flight, just fold them down for a tiny 38 cm packed length, plenty small enough to go inside your pack or case. Lightweight doesn't have to mean compromising comfort either, since the hollow, ladies'-specific Aergon grip is rounded all over and made for slimmer hands. Plus the extended Thermo Mid grip offers an instant change in length for varied terrain. Versatile, strong and highly packable; the Micro Vario Carbon Lady pole is the lightweight hiker's dream pole.

item.title: Cristallo Antishock
item.description: The superstrong Leki Cristallo Antishock screams durable comfort through every inch, from vented rubber handle to carbide tip. Tough aluminium tube makes up the body of this all-rounder of a trekking pole, ideal for hiking, trekking, ski-touring and more at any time of year. It's also secure - the Leki SpeedLock on the top joint offers quick, robust adjustment as you change terrain, whilst the SuperLock twist adjustment on the bottom joint holds a massive 140kg. The SuperLock has more tricks than that up its sleeve though, housing the SAS Lite sprung shock-absorbing system. This cushions your wrists from repeated impacts, supported as they are in the quick-drying air-textured straps. A great pole for use on hard surfaces and long journeys, the Cristallo Antishock will keep your hands comfortable all the way.

item.title: Softlite
item.description: The Leki Softlite trekking pole is lightweight and easy to use, but don't be thinking it's basic. No, this practical pole may be ideal for lightweight hiking, mountain marathons and ultralight backpacking, but it's also great for everything else too - from ambling up a munro to ski touring in the depths of winter. The poles' strength comes from the combination of high tensile strength aluminium with the reliable SpeedLock camming system. The pole itself is kept thin too, for even lower weight and a streamlined look. On top, the handle is shaped for comfort in most hands - soft rubber is vented and the tough wrist strap has a soft layer where it supports your wrist. So if you want one lightweight, reliable pole for all your self-propelled journeys, you can't go wrong with the Softlite by Leki.

item.title: Thermolite
item.description: Leki Thermolite trekking poles have the strength, durability and all-round good design to support your every hard challenge. Everything about them is selected for performance - the high grade aluminium alloy tubing, the SuperLock adjustment system and the Aergonomic foam handle all give it the substance and style of a pole to rely on. The SuperLock adjustment is a particular highlight when it comes to strength; holding 140kg at maximum strength it won't let you down once set. Then you have all-day comfort from the hand-shaped, moulded foam grip and air-textured, quick drying strap. A high-performing pole that will see you through many a tough day on mountains, hills and more.

item.title: Trail
item.description: The Leki Trail pole was made for where reliability and strength are critical - high alpine routes and remote expeditions. They're all about strength, with thicker-than average tube sections and Leki SuperLock adjusters to hold huge amounts of weight when you need them to. That's not to say that trekking comfort is ignored though - the Round Top Comfort grip with Soft rubber is shaped to work with most walkers' hands, reducing the amount of force needed to hold the pole. And the adjustable webbing wriststrap supports all day at minimal weight. Ideal for hard ascents and rough terrain, the Trail is what you need to depend upon when you're a long way from anywhere.

item.title: Cressida
item.description: The Leki Cressida trekking pole has the same design as the Leki Softlite, but it's smaller and lighter with a grip shaped for feminine hands. It's made for keeping you safely on your feet through challenging terrain, with SpeedLock adjusters that allow you to change the length in seconds to fit the gradient at every stage. The Cressida is kept lightweight and small-packing as well, so it fits easily on the outside of a smaller ladies' pack. And the foam grip is shaped specifically to accommodate a slim hand. Designed for ladies but with all the strength and support of the equivalent men's pole, the Cressida is ideal for all your big days out.

item.title: Easy Bag
item.description: The Leki Trekking Easy Bag is the easy way to carry your poles from place to place safely and without dirtying the inside of your car or case. Though when packed it takes up only a fist-sized space, this tough drawstring bag extends to 93cm to hold the longest collapsed trekking poles. Its two fastenings ensure a secure fit - a drawstring over the baskets and a webbing strap with buckle round the top. And the bottom section is made of tough fabric to stand up to those carbide tips. A must for anyone travelling with their poles, the Trekking Easy bag takes your sticks in style.

item.title: Supreme Shark
item.description: The Leki Supreme Shark Nordic Walking pole is Leki's premium aluminium pole, taking over from the Prestige for top-end performance at a reasonable price. Like all the adjustable poles in the range, the Supreme comes with two sections of strong aluminium, with the extremely strong SuperLock adjuster between them. But the natural cork grip and Trigger Shark glove attachment set the Supreme Shark apart from the rest. Cork gives you a cushioned, comfortable grip that manages moisture and avoids rubbing. And the Trigger Shark attachment adds ease of use and doesn't require a chunky piece of plastic hanging off your glove. In all, it's a versatile and comfortable pole ideal for tailoring to your perfect length for a long life of health-giving Nordic Walking.

item.title: Womens Trail Hiker Crew Grey Oyster UK 3.5-5.0
Womens Trail Hiker Crew Grey Oyster UK 5.5-7.5
Womens Trail Hiker Crew Grey Oyster UK 8.0-9.5
Tear-Aid Fabric Repair Pack
item.description: With a Storm Tear-Aid Fabric Repair Pack you can fix almost anything with a hole or tear - super-sticky, super-stretchy and airtight for instant repairs. Five small patches and two large bond to everything from canvas to fibreglass, through Dacron, polyurethane and neoprene. In fact about the only material you can't use it on is vinyl! You also get a full set of instructions and an alcohol wipe for preparing the surface. Once applied, you can use the item immediately as the adhesive is 90 percent bonded instantly, reaching full adhesion within an hour. It stretches and moves with the fabric too, so even if it's applied on an elbow or over an edge it's stay in place and well-stuck. Give damaged waterproofs, tents, rucksacks and more a new lease of life - Tear-Aid patches can be taken on every trip for instant permanent repairs even in the field.

item.title: Footwear Proofer 300ml
item.description: Storm Footwear Proofer does exactly what it says on the tin; no fuss, no worries, just quick restoration to your DWR's full performance. Quick and easy to apply through the aerosol spray format, a light coat on dry shoes dries in seconds and leaves no trace. Apart from causing water to bead up on the surface that is! The formula is as ecologically sound as is currently technically possible for a footwear proofer too, being based on C6 fluorocarbons (less harmful than the C8 fluorocarbons used in most DWR treatments). It's suitable for use on all footwear materials - fabrics, leather, Gore-Tex, even suede - and, once dry, you can't see or even feel it's there. Ideal for re-proofing your outdoor boots or shoes, but also for adding water-resistance to work shoes, fashion boots and pretty much anything else. A DWR exactly as it should be - quick, easy and effective so your feet stay dry for longer.

item.title: Deodoriser 75ml Spray
item.description: Kill the stink with Storm Deodoriser, a quick and easy way to keep your shoes, helmet, gloves and everything else smelling fresher for longer. Being based on a solution of silver ions, a couple of pumps of this effectively stop bacteria reproducing in your gear. And since it's their waste that does the smelling, the less bacteria there are, the less your kit stinks. Supplied in a handy-sized spray, the ideal is to give each item a quick spray while it's still warm after use. The first spray should last about a week, then the build-up effect makes subsequent treatments last longer. The more occasions you spray, the better it works. Any waterproofing on the inside won't be affected and the light fragrance immediately masks that warm feet smell so your kit bag or wardrobe doesn't cause asphyxiation. A smart solution for all those items that you dread taking off at the end of a warm day.

item.title: Fast Dry Proofer 500ml Spray
item.description: Storm Fast Dry Proofer does exactly that - restores or adds a DWR finish to tents, backpacks, clothing and any other fabric quickly, easily and eco-friendly-ly. It won't stain, dries at speed and leaves breathability untouched - sounds almost too good to be true, but we've seen it in action! The environmental credentials stem from the C6 fluorocarbons it's based on. These are less harmful than the C8 fluorocarbons used in most proofers if they get into water courses etc. Plus because it's in a handy spray can for direct application, less gets wasted between can and gear. It also doesn't require a heat treatment, so there's no energy used there either. It's as simple as spraying it evenly over the surface and leaving it to dry; add weather protection in minutes with Storm Fast Dry Proofer.

item.title: Eco+ Twin Pack 300ml
item.description: Try it and you'll love the ease and simplicity of the Storm Eco+ Twin Pack for cleaning and proofing all your outdoor clothes - in one wash! That's right, both products go in the washing machine drawer at the same time! And between them they remove dirt and reinstate the DWR coating on 2-3 garments of any type, all in one 30 degree cycle. There's no need to scrub your machine drawer or do an empty cycle beforehand either - the Storm Proofing system is designed to make it easy to look after your gear. But that's not the only advantage. The Storm Eco+ proofing system is also very environmentally friendly. That's because it has a C0 formulation that completely avoids the use of the potentially harmful fluorocarbons that you'll find in the majority of other proofers. The only trade-off is that your gear will need a bit of heat to cure the treatment - once dry, a spell on low in the tumble-dryer or under a cool iron (and a tea-towel) will do the trick. Having done this, your waterproofs, softshells, insulated clothes, gloves, fleeces or whatever you want to proof, will be just as water-repellent, if not more so, than when new. Plus it's actually more abrasion-resistant than other treatments in testing. Worth a try, wouldn't you say? Especially as 300ml will do four wash loads. Experience the future of DWR treatment with the Storm Proofing system.

item.title: Eco+ Twin Pack 75ml
item.description: Try it and you'll love the ease and simplicity of the Storm Eco+ Twin Pack for cleaning and proofing all your outdoor clothes - in one wash! That's right, both products go in the washing machine drawer at the same time! And between them they remove dirt and reinstate the DWR coating on 2-3 garments of any type, all in one 30 degree cycle. There's no need to scrub your machine drawer or do an empty cycle beforehand either - the Storm Proofing system is designed to make it easy to look after your gear. But that's not the only advantage. The Storm Eco+ proofing system is also very environmentally friendly. That's because it has a C0 formulation that completely avoids the use of the potentially harmful fluorocarbons that you'll find in the majority of other proofers. The only trade-off is that your gear will need a bit of heat to cure the treatment - once dry, a spell on low in the tumble-dryer or under a cool iron (and a tea-towel) will do the trick. Having done this, your waterproofs, softshells, insulated clothes, gloves, fleeces or whatever you want to proof, will be just as water-repellent, if not more so, than when new. Plus it's actually more abrasion-resistant than other treatments in testing. Worth a try, wouldn't you say? Experience the future of DWR treatment with the Storm Proofing system.

item.title: Eco+ Proofer 300ml Spray
item.description: The Storm Eco+ Proofer Spray allows directed application of a water-resistant DWR finish to virtually any fabric. Working with the Storm Cleaner it's environmentally friendly and easy to use. Simply spray evenly over damp or dry, clean fabric, drip dry and then cure in the tumble dryer. The result is an effective water-repellent finish to your waterproofs, softshell, fleece, walking trousers or almost anything else you can get in a tumble dryer. It's actually more abrasion-resistant than other treatments, believe it or not. And because it's C0 ie fluorocarbon-free, it's not going to harm the environment. Is there anything more you could want? Keep your gear at its best without harming the environment, the Storm Eco+ Proofer Spray makes light work of blocking heavy weather.

item.title: Eco+ Proofer 300ml
item.description: Storm Eco+ Proofer forms the business end of the Storm Proofing System, giving you an easily applied but highly effective DWR for virtually any fabric. Designed for use in your washing machine, it goes in the drawer at the same time as the Storm Cleaner for cleaning and proofing in one cycle. But it's ecologically sound as well as straightforward to use. Completely free of fluorocarbons, PFOA and PFOS, the dendromer-based technology is approved by Greenpeace. It lasts longer than some other treatments because it'se more abrasion-resistant. And because only one cycle is needed, it uses less water than other systems. Plus it's more economical, giving you four wash loads of 2-3 garments out of each 300ml bottle. The only trade-off is the need for heat to cure the treatment - once dry, a spell on low in the tumble-dryer or under a cool iron (and a tea-towel) will do the trick. It's ideal for anything you want to repel water (as long as it fits in your washing machine) - hardshells, softshells, fleeces, windshells and more. An easy to use, eco-friendly proofer that will stay in place for longer - is this the ideal product for maintaining your waterproof gear?

item.title: Cleaner 300ml
item.description: Storm Cleaner gently but effectively cleans all your technical outdoor gear without excess foam or stubborn residues being left on your clothes. It also forms part of the Storm Proofing system - if you put Storm Proofer into the fabric softener section of the washer you can do both in one wash cycle and save water. That's because it's pH neutral, so even in hard water you don't get the reaction that leaves those streaky white marks. You can also use it to handwash individual or bulky items like rucksacks. Totally PFC-free and happiest at 30 degrees, Storm Cleaner is the eco-friendly cleaner for all your outdoor gear.

item.title: Octane XCT Blue Jewel/Bright Fuschia 6.5 Litres
All Clear System 0.75L
item.description: With the Camelbak All Clear purification system you have UV water treatment and storage facilities in one handy package - ideal for minimalist and fast-moving trips. Not only is it compact, the All Clear system is quick and easy to use too - no pumping, tablets or waiting around. Simply fill, switch on and agitate for 60 seconds for reliably safe drinking water. There are a couple of provisos - the water must be clear for the UV light to penetrate, but there's a pre-filter available separately that helps stop debris getting in when you're out in the wilds. And it's not too happy at freezing temperatures, so you'll have to keep it in your jacket if you're going somewhere cold. But apart from those it's ready for anything, deactivating viruses and protozoa as well as bacteria from springs, streams, taps and any other sources you find on your travels. It also comes with a case and simple cap so you can protect the treatment cap on the move. A seriously useful bit of kit to avoid carrying all your water on your back, the All Clear system makes it safer to rely on nature.

item.title: All Clear Pre-Filter
item.description: The Camelbak All Clear Pre-Filter sits neatly over the neck of your All Clear bottle while filling, to keep your water as clean as possible for treatment. The All Clear system works effectively only on water that's clear and without 'bits', so it's important to keep your water as clean as possible from the very start. Not only does this sturdy pre-filter prevent debris like sediment, insects, plant parts and worse from getting into your bottle. It's also a safeguard that protects the threaded neck from the untreated water, adding to your safety. A vital addition to your All Clear system when you'll be filling it from streams and rivers etc on a remote trip.

item.title: Antidote 3L
item.description: The CamelBak 3L Antidote Reservoir is a fully featured water reservoir with a low profile design and centre baffling, it offers excellent stability and easy pack loading. The Quick Link System allows the tube to disconnect cleanly and uses an auto shut-off feature to stop any drips or spills from one end while the Big Bite Valve mouth piece self-seals immediately after use on the other. The taste of the water is kept pure and fresh using CamelBak's PureFlow Tube, thus ensuring your drink stays refreshing and doesn't carry the 'plastic' taste of some other systems. More than fresh tasting, the Antidote uses HydroGuard technology to provide anti-microbial protection. This is accomplished by inhibiting the growth of bacteria that can often cause odours, discolouration and deterioration of the bottle.

item.title: Cleaning Brush Kit
item.description: The CamelBak Cleaning Brush Kit is the ideal cleaning solution for your water reservoir system. The Brush Kit comes with a flexible tube brush to thread all the way through the tube for easy cleaning and a specially designed reservoir brush; with a deliberate bend in to make it easy to clean the entire inner surface.

item.title: Ultra Light Hiking Over Calf Quarry Grey UK 3.5-5
Chalk Bag Belt
item.description: The DMM Chalk Bag Belt is a useful replacement that fits the Tube, Traction and Trad chalkbags, or most other chalkbags in existence. Once threaded, your chalkbag will sit comfortably in the small of your back, or round the side or even at the front for those off-width cracks. Supplied in assorted colours (call if you need a particular colour), to coordinate or compliment your existing kit, it's just as suitable for holding your trousers up, with a lightweight webbing buckle for security. A handy spare or vital accessory for every climbing trip.
